6902628.title: one-third mile hill repeats
6902628.description: After running my hill loop I still felt good, so decided to do some hill repeats, full recovery in-between (HR back to 120).  Splits:  2:06 / 2:06 / 2:00 / 1:59.  This was WAY better than the last time I did hill repeats (about a month ago).  Feeling fit and loving the Altra Running shoes.

32894410.description: tempo / long interval 2. Heat was getting to me, got some blisters behind my big toes in my VFF.
32894410.title: shortest Lake Alice loop

31144369.description: Tejas Trails Wild Hare 25k trail race. Great tough course with lots of slippery mud on the ups and downs. Earned 3rd overall in 1:55:08. Finished before the thunderstorms came through. I heard that the 50 mile race turned into more of a survival run.
31144369.title: Tejas Trails Wild Hare 25k race

31933425.title: Five Points of Life Marathon
31933425.description: Five Points of Life Marathon race. Official time 3:12:50 (Boston Qualifier!), Masters Winner, PR by over 13 minutes, top-10, and just a few places out of the overall cash prizes. Would not have done this without the last 6 miles of pacing from Matthew Howland. I was trying to run without any gels or sugar but started to cramp in the hammies near mile 20. Strawberry Banana Gu drove the cramping away. I had 3 possible goals going into the race... 1. break 3 hours, or 2. run a BQ, or 3. get a PR.  Glad I was able to hit my intermediate goal but wow, the marathon is a beast. Probable Splits: 6:40, 7:04, 7:16, 7:16, 7:02, 6:53, 7:06, 7:10, 7:15, 6:50, 6:25, 7:46, 7:19, 7:19, 7:45, 7:45, 7:23, 7:34, 7:04, 7:42, 7:42. 8:00, 8:00, 7:48, 8:05, 7:45

19864393.title: The Daily
19864393.description: Glad to be home again in Florida. Just a little run to stretch my legs.

3247483.title: easy 3 barefoot
3247483.description: After wearing ankle support all day for 3 days (took it off at night), the tenderness around my Achilles tendon went away.  Nice easy barefoot run to get the stiffness out.  After the run I have a little tenderness again so will continue to ice and take it easy, but I think I'm ok to start doing eccentric strength exercises.

6565555.description: Faster than I've been going on my long easy days, but I was able to hang with it. Nice cool morning.  Altra Instincts are "Dan Stoner - Approved!" for San Felasco and Florida trails.
6565555.title: San Felasco 2x outer loop with Dan C.

4918606.title: easy greenway warmup for PT
4918606.description: The wet packed sand felt good under my VFF.  Going slow enough and short enough that I didn't get any rubbed raw spots.

26536357.description: Cold morning. Liking my VFF SeeYa so far.
26536357.title: incline intervals

9906322.description: So many carbs this weekend and leftover cookies lying around the house (not anymore), had to get out there and burn off some energy.
9906322.title: barefoot pleasant evening

29051636.title: Sunday Runday
29051636.description: Small group tonight (just me and Herb).  Perhaps the severe thunderstorms and HAIL scared people off!

23943311.description: Soggy! Pushed a little on the way back. Splits: 38:57, 31:14
23943311.title: Santa Fe water stop out-and-back

34057400.description: First loop was sociable with a group, lots of stories from recent races. I ran 2nd and 3rd loops by myself. Estimated time on first loop (Blue+Yellow outside): 1:13:14. 2nd loop (Yellow): 50:28. 3rd loop (Yellow) 45:15. Just over 8 minutes per mile avg. on last loop. Oh yeah, and first run in Inov-8 TrailRoc 245. A great shoe, no issues, the 3mm drop didn't bother me, perfect if I ever need a rock plate.
34057400.title: San Felasco trails

27587472.description: Still feel like I am training on tired legs.
27587472.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

16602077.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

34680806.title: Ocala Marathon
34680806.description: I put in a good race at the Ocala Marathon. Kept myself under control and "easy" for the first half, able to finish the second half a little faster. Best part is that I was able to put on pants afterward without having any muscle cramps. Fueled with combination of gels and bananas (BOO! none of the aid stations had gel as advertised). Weather forecast was changing all week, turned out to be nice morning! Rain stayed away, temps dropped a degree during the run, and there was a nice "breeze" (gusts up to 15 - 20 mph). Beautiful course through horse country. Splits: 7:34, 7:35, 7:51, 8:02, 7:34, 7:14, 7:43, 7:38, 7:41, 7:46, 7:26, 7:50, 7:09*, 7:06* (* Got a little carried away after turning a corner and getting a nice cooling wind), 7:20, 7:38, 7:34, 7:58, 7:44, 8:24** (** Stopped for a Twizzler), 7:45, 7:45, ? something something Finish!

32808655.description: Sore quads and HOT but otherwise a good run.
32808655.title: south campus

15545978.description: Merrell Trail Gloves are a nice addition to my collection. Out: 50:43, Back: 40:44. I still think this is longer than the 9 miles that my GPS told me once upon a time.
15545978.title: no sidewalks

23229311.title: University Ave 6mi loop
23229311.description: My schedule almost let me run with the Sunday Runday crew... almost.

31844287.title: recovery
31844287.description: Left pain near the medial malleolus flared up pretty bad. While running I can't differentiate between this and Achilles tendon pain, but if I reach down and poke the Achilles it is fine. So *that* is good news. Just need to keep the recovery going. Five Points is a little over a week away!

33336093.description: Barefoot. Final Pi (3.14) miles at 8:16 pace. Possibly a little bit much on hot sidewalks considering how little barefoot running I have been doing lately.
33336093.title: barefoot around campus

30551446.title: easy with steep hill sprints
30551446.description: After getting over the hungover feeling, felt good. Just a little tiredness in my upper quads / hip extenders. Included 5 x steep hill sprints.

26397394.title: barefoot
26397394.description: Some trail but mostly sidewalk. Barefoot easy. Fighting a headache this morning. Longest run since October.

34506896.description: putting in a few easy miles while suffering from sinus issues
34506896.title: sick

3071377.description: I'm happy with this performance for a first race.  Hope the official times get posted somewhere... I didn't pay close attention at the end (too busy sprinting) but I'm pretty sure I was under 23 minutes.  Did not see any other Vibrams out there. The VFF Bikila did great as a road racing shoe.
3071377.title: Project Haiti 5k race in VFF Bikilas

36661434.title: Track workout 2 x 800m, 2 x 600m, 1 x 500m
36661434.description: Track workout 2 x 800m, 2 x 600m, 1 x 500m. 200m rest in between each. Toes in VFF were cold by the end! Splits: 800m - 2:56, 2:57, 600m - 2:13, 2:12, 500m - 1:44

33797492.description: Barefoot is Best. After doing the blue loop with trail shoes and feeling pains in my right foot, decided to go barefoot rather than calling it quits. The trails were damp and soft, a rare opportunity with so few sharp pointy things. Foot felt fine. Still some sore parts in other areas of my legs. Nice run!
33797492.title: San Felasco yellow loop - barefoot

11940624.title: no sidewalks
11940624.description: Felt pretty low towards the end. Clearly still recovering from holiday carb overload and the first week back at work, need to get back on the fat burning train and get more sleep. I kept the insoles in my Instincts, thinking that maybe they will last longer that way.  But I don't like them as much with the soft insole and I tend to feel pains further up the legs and even my feet don't feel as good.

34560219.title: Florida Track Club - Shorter Mile race
34560219.description: First run of the Florida Track Club - Shorter Mile road race on New Year's day. Not bad given recent training, sickness, and travel. Very warm and humid. Finished in 5:25. Splits: 1:15, 1:22, 1:25, 1:22.

5437317.description: Got a few barefoot steps in while waiting for the grill to heat up.  Finally, a week-day run while the sun was still up!!!
5437317.title: easy barefoot

33199419.description: Cemetery Ridge and Chestnut trails at Clear Creek Metro Park. Great trails about 5 minutes from my parents' house. Max Grade 23.3%. Altitude Gain 756 ft. Steep climbs made me practice my uphill power walking. Time includes all of the stops to take pictures along the way. Nice cool pleasant morning!
33199419.title: Clear Creek Metro Park trails

6785274.title: meh
6785274.description: Thought I'd feel good after taking a couple of days off. At first I thought it was going to be a good run but instead I felt stiff in a lot of strange places, generally tired.  Maybe mental.

16045022.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

7264861.title: no sidewalks
7264861.description: Many non-running things going on over this past week.  It payed to ease back on the running during time of stress... had a good run this morning.

9211275.title: First run in Moc3
9211275.description: Dare I say it? The best minimalist shoe yet?  Ok ok, too early to tell after just one run... but I very much enjoyed the Moc3.  Closest to barefoot of any of my minimalist shoes (this includes huarache sandals and VFF Bikila).  Able to easily feel the ground and maintain my barefoot running form.  No cushion, just some protection.  Great forefoot shape and fit.  No silly toe pockets.  Happy with this shoe.

5960912.title: Easy shakeout run in VFF
5960912.description: Good to feel the ground again (after so many runs in NB Minimus).

27561582.description: Took a longer route to the track to get in extra miles. Speedwork included:  1. a long gradual uphill surge heading east past Lake Alice.  2. 800m of stride straights, jog curves.  Accelerated up to near full sprint on each. 3.  2 x 800m interval. I was going to do repeat miles but since I ran the first one too fast I settled for 800s. Still recovering from marathon do not want to risk an injury. Splits: 2:56, 2:50
27561582.title: Track day

6215015.title: warmup
6215015.description: Hamstrings still a little sore from PT.

35385637.title: Hill Sprints x 8
35385637.description: Felt Hot today. Hill sprints were good. Also stopped at the track to run a couple 200m sprints with Richard G. He's fast(!) so we are starting to work on extending his speed.

1980599.description: CALVES!  1.5 mi of this was barefoot.

5041060.description: Hopefully my last session of PT.  I wore my huarache sandals today and caused a little bit of a stir.
5041060.title: warmup before PT

31011120.description: Tempo run on tired legs. Campus loop x 2 for 10 miles total in 1:05:30. Slits for each 5 mile loop: 32:39, 32:50. avg. 6:33 pace per mile. Taper time!
31011120.title: Campus Tempo Loop

21173396.description: I am working on two major changes to my form (hip extension and lifting the hip to keep it from dipping down).  This included a 1.5 mile temp in the middle, 8:46 (5:50 per mile pace).
21173396.title: work run

23846652.title: Track workout 8 x 1200m
23846652.description: A good workout on already sore legs. 2 minutes rest easy jog in between each rep. Splits: 4:36, 4:40, 4:46, 4:44, 4:32, 4:36, 4:31, 4:34

17247103.title: greenway plus brywood hills
17247103.description: My first run in new Skora Form shoes. These are the Skoras made of fancy leather that I picked up with huge discount at The Clymb. Unfortunately, they are a little bit large when I take out the insole and I had some rubbing on the big toe just ahead of the ball of my foot. Otherwise, they make a great minimal shoe have good traction on trail surfaces. My legs were sore during the day from yesterday's stadium stair workout, but they loosened up pretty quickly and didn't seem to bother me during the run. It was very hot today but my Sweat GUTR is working great to keep the drips out of my eyes.

31835401.title: drizzle
31835401.description: First run in Altra Instinct 3.0. Nice shoes! Added some uptempo in the middle. 3.6 at 8:30 pace, 3.7 at 7:45 pace. Couldn't muster much more. Glutes were tired.

31983670.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
31983670.description: Pushed the middle section (under 8-min pace). I was able to get good turnover and decent drive on the uphills. Altra Instinct 3.0 with no insoles are great.

25327305.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

32994501.title: Track meet 1500m
32994501.description: Gainesville track series at Cone Park. I was 4 times as old as each of my opponents. 1500m race in 4:53. Splits: 53s (300m), 1:19, 1:22, 1:18.

29734621.title: Levees
29734621.description: Feeling last night's beers. Merrell Vapor Glove has a tread pattern that loves to get full mud and wet sand.

32252985.title: good morning
32252985.description: Felt pretty good today. Maybe the new allergy meds.

35162000.title: steep hill sprints
35162000.description: Easy then 8 x steep hill sprints. Felt sluggish.

23908570.description: Ran laps while the kids played at the playground.
23908570.title: Cone Park track

25302774.description: I was getting ready for my LONG run this morning when I turned around to find my youngest daughter sitting there in her running clothes. She said "I want to run with you!" How could I say "no" to that?  We ran around our neighborhood together in the dark for a little bit before I sat her down with breakfast and then I finished packing up to hit the trails of San Felasco. I ran from the south side hiking trails to the north side horse trails. I explored some of the mountain bike trails such as "Hidden Rise". I only saw two groups of riders and otherwise had the north side trails to myself. I am kind of estimating pace and distance, but this was definitely my lifetime longest run ever!   Weather was nice with a breeze and light mist much of the morning. Nature today included a snake that I almost stepped on, I think it was a cottonmouth! Now, two weeks of recovery before my 50k race.
25302774.title: San Felasco trails LONG run

11518384.description: I was excited about this run. I went off-call at 5pm, pager OFF!  Still didn't get out the door to run until after dark, but that's why I wear my Soft Star Moc3s.
11518384.title: 39th Ave Loop

28785855.description: Warm today. Hill sprints with previous coworker.  We are going to try to make it a weekly thing.
28785855.title: campus easy and 5 x steep hill sprints

36054778.description: Steep hill sprints x 9 reps.  They cut the trees down on NW 9th Place so no more shade.  Running at noon we opted for the 8th Ave. hill.
36054778.title: steep hill sprints

22857566.title: greenway
22857566.description: Had to walk it in. Developed some pain in my left upper / outer glute and knee. Too much idle time being sick I guess.

13821359.description: Thinking about turning this into a daily thing.
13821359.title: easy short morning run

31323702.title: Gainesville Brewery Run 5k race
31323702.description: Nice day to run the Gainesville Brewery Run 5k race and drink a boot full of beer! Great venue at First Magnitude Brewery and the Gainesville-Hawthorne paved trail. 2nd place overall with a time of 17:38.

25799042.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

32945332.description: Hosting a run through campus with a few interested hackathon participants.
32945332.title: hackathon run through campus

22185011.title: easy track work
22185011.description: 20 minutes of stride the straights, jog the curves. Didn't keep track of laps or distance. Had a nice chat with Daniel Akers about all things running.

24996082.title: Brywood to 13th St
24996082.description: My knee and pinky toe (bashed by a trail tripping incident) felt ok today.

30712960.description: legs still carrying some tiredness from the weekend.
30712960.title: long warmup

12911884.description: Hurray for running!  Only felt a tiny soreness in the ribs during the last mile or so, about the same time I started feeling a twinge in my foot.  Shuffled in the last bit just to be safe and keep the foot issue in check but really glad to have a decent run under my belt.
12911884.title: 39th Ave Loop

24706405.title: San Felasco trails
24706405.description: I guess this was day 1 of Ultra training. Time to start thinking about the shoes and equipment I will use for the 50k. Tried my Altra Lone Peak trail shoes thinking I might want the extra cushion but they are probably just too much shoe for me on the typical Florida trail.

36099614.description: Easing back into running due to Piriformis Syndrome.
36099614.title: longer round trip to track

4631228.title: flat 8th ave
4631228.description: Concentrated on form.  When I get it right (like tonight) these runs are therapeutic for my Achilles tendon issue.

4195439.title: San Felasco Blue loop
4195439.description: Pretty spent by the time I started this.  Managed to finish, making today my new longest running day with 17.8 miles total.

16921976.title: run in the rain
16921976.description: My quads were sore all day today from the weekend runs so I took this one easy.

2441987.description: Mostly on shady trails but some sidewalk and road.  Concentrated on form, trying to avoid blisters from 4pm hot surfaces.  I did get some blisters but at least none of them ripped open.  I guess this means my technique is getting better.  Running without pain certainly helps, too.  It was nice to feel the trail under my bare feet again.
2441987.title: Yay for barefoot

25650857.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

35837208.title: Bull Creek greenbelt
35837208.description: Some steep climbs and descents. Made it out early this morning so I turned into a sweatball but was not uncomfortably hot.

5422797.description: This is an out-and-back route.  Ran 19:05 out, 15:52 back.  Nice evening.  VFF felt good.
5422797.title: 8th Ave short flat

29680807.title: barefoot first run back
29680807.description: First run back after hiatus. Nice easy barefoot.

32245118.description: Did some running by myself and included some tempo work. Then ran a yellow loop with Matt C. Just what I needed. Love my inov-8 Trailroc 235 shoes. Best trail shoe ever!
32245118.title: San Felasco trails

8841704.description: Altra Zero Drop shoes are great for running stadium stairs in The Swamp.  Despite the dripping, burning sweat in my eyes had a great workout.  5 x stairs.
8841704.title: Stadium Stairs at The Swamp

4117179.description: Perfect night for a run.  Air was slightly cool and damp from earlier rains.  I was perhaps a bit over ambitious on this one... the last 30 minutes were rough.
4117179.title: My longest run in VFF

4230186.description: My dad brought some old video tape from my college cross country days... watched to see my running form from way back then.  Inspired me to go run a little faster.
4230186.title: 2 mile personal time trial

32783882.description: greenway trails with 2 x half mile repeats on twisty single track. Some super sticky slippery mud through one section. Splits:4:13, 4:02
32783882.title: greenway trails with half mile repeats

27497614.title: San Felasco trails
27497614.description: Cool foggy morning, great day to run on the trails!  Lots of hills today. Sadly, had to cut my run short since I developed a bit of a knot in my left quad.  Perhaps too much too soon after the marathon.  But all is well, having a delicious breakfast of farmers market fare.

20881675.description: Got my run in between rain showers. Warm and very humid. Way off my target pace.
20881675.title: Tempo on Waldo Rd. bike path

29347393.description: Nice group of people out tonight in the HEAT.
29347393.title: Lloyd Clarke Sunday Runday

7127854.description: Felt cool this morning.  Did my "Brywood hills" and "no sidewalks" routes.  The trails were nice and soft from all of the rain.  The forests were happy.  Just drank water before and during, I was glad to get some coffee in me when I got home.
7127854.title: Recovery run

7320372.title: downhill sprints
7320372.description: At least four repeat .2 mile downhill sprints.  Goofed on the watch but I think splits were around 56-57 seconds each.  Felt a bit awkward running that fast downhill but I could feel the increase in leg turnover.

20050979.title: anti-insanity run
20050979.description: Other than the fact I forgot how to run and my knee hurt due to the first few steps pounding away at the pavement... this was a great little walk/jog to get the blood flowing and stem my insanity. Definitely going to run tomorrow.

25826206.description: Finished my run and all is right with the world... despite the fact that my foot is still gimpy.  It is actually starting to feel a little better each day but I figured I ought to tag the Injured face so I had a record of it.
25826206.title: Brywood hills

34720363.description: Just me, my thoughts, the trees, and the trail. Seems like forever since I have run on the local greenways. Very enjoyable run. I developed some pain in my right foot, reminiscent of the cuboid syndrome issue I had last year, which is concerning but I am not too worried about only because I have had it before.
34720363.title: Greenway trails

9162731.description: Included two passes over my "favorite" barefoot coaching surface (perhaps "terribly effective" is a better choice of words).
9162731.title: barefoot night run

32548714.description: LGAA 5k race, we (Youth Combine) won the fastest team competition! I finished in 18:27 on a warm evening for the age group win, but am a little disappointed with my race. Splits: 5:42, 6:01, 6:12
32548714.title: LGAA 5k race

6002831.title: Easy RunAmocs
6002831.description: Just loosening up after yesterday's race.

33125817.description: Nice race in my hometown on a cool damp evening. 3rd Annual Our Town 5k. Pleased with my 2nd place finish overall and a time of 17:53. Splits: 5:25, 6:16, 6:12 (last 1.1 mi)
33125817.title: Our Town 5k race

31260701.title: San Felasco MTB trails
31260701.description: Finished riding about 12 miles on my mountain bike and then went for a run in my new Topo Oterro shoes to test them out. So far... I like!  Also.. EPIC Bars are awesome! I like the Bison and Lamb the best. Two test runs so far where I eat the bar and then start running, the best part is NO BURPS like so many other fueling options. I think I may have found my shoe and fuel options for next year's 40+ mile Ultra!

22621058.description: And about a mile of warmup on the track, including a few intervals with the early group.
22621058.title: short round trip UF track

15617770.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
15617770.description: Thank you Altra Sampsons for reminding me how to run. Tonight was the happiest my Achilles tendons have been in a long long long time. The technique adjustments seem to be paying off.

34068219.title: Track workout ladder down
34068219.description:
Nice cool morning for a track workout. Super sore calves. Had some tightness / weakness in my hip flexors.  Hung through the whole workout, even splits between the two sets of 1200m, 800m, 400m, 200m, 200m (200m rest between reps, 400m rest between sets)
Set 1: 4:06, 2:39, 1:16, 34, 34 | Set 2: 4:06, 2:39, 1:15, 34, 32

18751973.title: Work to Morningside Nature Center
18751973.description: With two outer loops at Morningside. Felt hot and BLAH today.

27063522.description: Legs a little sore from yesterday's race but otherwise ok. Turnout was a little low this evening!
27063522.title: Sunday Runday

19209666.title: Austin Cary Memorial Forest run
19209666.description: A nice run at the forest in my new Altra Superior trail shoes. 3 x 5k. Splits: 24:50, 24:19, 24:12

13934442.title: second run of the day
13934442.description: Ate too much of this evil trail mix stuff (mostly chocolate and partially hydrogenated oils), had to get out there again and burn off some of that crap.  Nice mileage for the day.

17632982.title: warmup and cooldown for track workout

35373143.title: no sidewalks
35373143.description: Temps started in the 80s and went up from there. At least there was a breeze so it didn't actually feel terrible.

22095800.description: Felt terrific and pushed the pace a little. One yellow loop (46:02 for 5.6 miles) and one blue loop (38:34 for 4.8 miles).
22095800.title: San Felasco trails

34937419.description: Stadium stairs. 2 x stairs, 2 x benches (30 - top).
34937419.title: stadium stairs

15942101.description: Just trying to get through another on-call week.  These seem to sap my energy.
15942101.title: same as last night

30179096.title: Mid-day campus run
30179096.description: Took advantage of the breezy day. Ended up at a moderate pace for the 2nd half.

30215508.description: Worked up to a moderate pace before heading to the track. Aborted the strides on the track after trying the first few... my glutes are very sore today.
30215508.title: Moderate and easy

3160102.description: Nice barefoot run on the trails.  Forgot to stop my watch.  Saw lots of friendly faces this morning and had a bigger group than usual.  Cathy B. - sorry I couldn't hang longer and do another loop.
3160102.title: San Felasco (Millhopper)

33515332.description: I almost did a faceplant coming back into my neighborhood. Ball of my foot slammed square into a raised edge of pavement in the dark, due to ongoing construction...
33515332.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

18992599.description: Managed 12 reps on the press-box side, with a short jog along the bottom row of bleachers in between each rep. Didn't push hard at all but definitely got the heart rate up.
18992599.title: Stadium stairs

33060837.title: hot up and up
33060837.description: including half mile of stride straights on track.

19785690.title: fields and woods
19785690.description: I think this is my longest run since the marathon.  Noticed a little stiffness in the same hip spot as before. Ran around the High School cross country course in my home town.  23 degrees at the start, everything was crunchy. Altra Superiors make a good snow running shoe, plenty of room for thick socks and they dry quickly for the next day's outing.

28568774.title: nice cool morning
28568774.description: Noticeable pain in my right foot. Injury still present and more noticeable when I wear cushioned shoes.

10904653.title: cool and brisk
10904653.description: Had to cut this run short. Peristalsis always wins.

35390732.description: Track workout 2 x 2 mile. Allergies are still killing me but ran consistent splits: 11:56, 11:55
35390732.title: Track workout 2 x 2 mile

22403854.description: First run in new Altra "The One" shoes.  Hard not to go fast in new speedy shoes.
22403854.title: University Ave 6mi loop

10212313.description: Hard day at work.  Huge lunch.  Huge dinner with beer and ice cream for dessert.  Did some sprints but also walked some.
10212313.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

32506890.description: Heat training. Wore SKINS tights, shorts, compression t-shirt, long-sleeve turtleneck, cotton gloves and winter hat. Surged 3 hills to make sure my temps got way up there. I warmed up so quickly that I didn't really notice any of my sore muscles. :)
32506890.title: Heat Training

8818101.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
8818101.description: I survived another heat acclimation run.

18269195.description: First run in a few weeks where I felt really good.
18269195.title: The Daily

24816572.title: San Felasco trails to cap my first 70 mile week
24816572.description: Dailymile is going to show over 60 miles but really I had 70 if I count Sunday thru Saturday (today). Either way, this has been the highest mileage week of my life. Tomorrow is a rest day.  ;)

31618929.description: Alternating easy and moderate and then pushed a little the last few. Stoked about my pace today (avg. 6:45 per mile)! Now... for breakfast steak!
31618929.title: long run

5851783.title: Long run in RunAmocs
5851783.description: I have been re-reading the Lydiard, decided I needed to get in some 2-hour endurance-building runs.  Wanted to try doing a long run in my RunAmocs.  Ran on greenway / trails where I could, including Clear Lake Nature Area where I had never been before. RunAmocs worked fine.  Not exactly sure of the distance or pace.

27397747.description: Finished my second marathon, the Five Points of Life. My own performance wasn't anything special (not in shape!) but I feel great that I was able to help a lady named Nina get her BQ! We ran together for a lot of the second half and it helped me a lot to work together during that long stretch on Williston Rd. I helped pull her through the last mile and she made her BQ time by 10 seconds!
27397747.title: Five Points of Life Marathon race

28852537.title: great barefoot run
28852537.description: Felt great! Some hot spots on the bottom of my feet from the brisk pace and then I had to run through the construction debris along 16th Ave. Planning to take a few more easy days but the deep soreness in my quads is gone!

34083706.description: Had to push the last 15 minutes at tempo effort (6:50 pace) to get home on time.
34083706.title: small group run

24156505.description: Didn't get started until 8 am so it was sunny and hot by finish time at 11am. This was a tough one.
24156505.title: LSD

32467222.description: Very warm and humid. Some sunshine. Surged the hills and then felt like keeping up the faster pace.
32467222.title: campus

12670473.title: LSD barefoot
12670473.description: With this run I passed 200 miles barefoot.  Powered by kid's birthday cake, tried to get moving before the sugar coma set in. My ribs are finally healed enough I could run (slowly).  Going barefoot helped reduce the jarring, too.  Felt pretty warm today.  Longest barefoot run in a while.

21554443.title: Lloyd Clarke Sunday Runday
21554443.description: Met up with the Lloyd Clarke crew for Sunday Runday. I ran / walked with my daughter. She was very competitive and had a few good surges to keep from getting passed. Then a side stitch got her going up the steep hill to 8th Ave so we mostly walked back to the store. She ran almost a full mile before needing to stop. Lots of potential there. :)

31788332.title: Newnan's Lake 15k race
31788332.description: Once again a beautiful cold morning for the Newnan's Lake 15k race. My fastest ever at this distance with a PR by over a minute and a half... really good considering my legs were definitely not feeling fresh (marathon training). Age Group Winner. Finish time: 58:20  Splits: 5:48, 6:23, 6:16, 6:31, 6:51, 6:05, 6:12, 6:12, 6:12, 1:43

28347121.description: Pushed hard on the long uphills.
28347121.title: cool morning

36477060.description: Focused on coming down stairs slowly, maximizing eccentric muscle and tendon action.
36477060.title: stadium stairs

11651408.description: Altra Adams again.  Holiday vacation is nice.
11651408.title: Altra Adams yet again

19197452.description: Nice easy run on the greenway trails. Legs and feet were pretty stiff this morning.
19197452.title: greenway trails

30355319.description: A touch sore in the knees from mountain biking. Wore Altra The One for the first time in a long time.  No pain in my sesamoids.
30355319.title: campus workday run

32504275.description: Sore muscles from Thursday's track workout. Loosening up with a nice barefoot run!
32504275.title: The Daily

3273568.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
3273568.description: Ran with friend Matt.  It was super humid after the rain... the breeze didn't seem to help at all.  Felt very "blah".  Seemed to take a lot of effort but I know we were not going very fast.

33044868.description: Hot! 6 x long stairs, 6 x short stairs sprints.
33044868.title: stadium stairs

21640605.title: morning
21640605.description: I planned to run longer and harder but had a strange night last night, woke up with a fever or something. Decided to just put in a few easy miles.

6543052.description: Still pretty warm and humid out there.  Felt tired.  Here are notables from earlier in the day... work was blah, ate a big lunch (Indian buffet), skipped my Workrave (lots of sitting today), steak was part of dinner.
6543052.title: long night loop

17149917.title: Track workout
17149917.description: Track workout 4x200m, 2x800m, 4x200m. Stephanie has some speed. Splits: 38,43,37,38 (200m), 2:53, 2:46 (800m), 37,36,36,33 (200m). A good, hard effort.

11569523.description: Nice little run in Altra Adams before breakfast. Ran in socks and without the insoles which seems to make them the most comfortable for running.
11569523.title: exploring in Altra Adams

10366002.description: Still some soreness from my last race so going to continue taking it easy for a while. Spent time visualizing myself running fast. Trying out some form things. Looking forward to busting out some good times this fall/winter/spring.
10366002.title: easy focus on technique

9584056.title: barefoot at noon
9584056.description: Hot. Barefoot. Breezy. Good.  The new boardwalks in Ring Park are really nice.

27663749.title: UF SW Rec Center
27663749.description: Took the opportunity to use the free access during spring break to check out the UF RecSports facilities.  Did some running on their indoor "track" and lifted weights.

30495269.title: trying on shoes
30495269.description: Shipments from Zappos. Jogging around the house trying to figure out which shoes to keep and which ones to send back.  Keeping Altra 3-Sum for sure.

18992700.description: Wanted to try out the Altra Samsons on the track. I liked them a lot, I might start doing my track workouts in them. Ran 69 seconds for 400m (this after doing stadium stairs).
18992700.title: one 400m on the UF track

32730173.description: Short but intense. 4 x stadium stairs, 4 x first flight sprints, 2 x uphill strides.
32730173.title: stadium stairs and hills

6335541.description: I do not like that increasing intensity aggravates my Achilles tendon area.  I do like that my endurance training seems to be working.
6335541.title: long night loop

9095919.description: Mid-day trail run.  Was planning to do a whole lot more but some muscles are still complaining about last week's mountain running. Sore muscles combined with the heat, I decided to call it quits.
9095919.title: San Felasco blue loop

10754851.title: RunAmoc DASHing
10754851.description: Nice cool evening.  Started feeling a blister between ball of my foot and big toe, maybe leftover from my last barefoot run.  I was even wearing my Injinji socks.  Otherwise, the run went well until I bit the dust on an uneven sidewalk.

2032050.description: Ran in my new huarache sandals.  Still some discomfort around the toes, will continue to tweak the lacing.  They definitely force a barefoot style run and I love the extra traction.  I went slow to concentrate on form.  For the first time I felt a glimmer, just a glimmer, of what I'll be able to do if I get in shape.
2032050.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway

29793559.description: Added a couple fartleks of 1:36, 2:22. Sore today in odd places dueb to kettlebell swings yesterday.
29793559.title: Fartleks

10869852.title: morning run in Bare-X 150
10869852.description: Tried again with the insoles installed. Took them out halfway through. I like them better without.

31912577.title: 8th Ave short flat
31912577.description: Picked it up to 7:40 in the middle. Have a cold or something and feeling tired.

30304763.title: Track 5 x 1600m
30304763.description: You might call this the first day of half marathon training. Track workout 5 x 1600m with 400m recovery. Nice and consistent splits: 6:24, 6:23, 6:20, 6:22, 6:21

23774260.title: Stadium stairs
23774260.description: It was hot and very humid at 11am this morning. My plan was to try to complete an hour of stadiums, full stairs, easy pace but no stops at the top or bottom. Reality check. I only managed 13 minutes, 7 repeats. There is a lot of training opportunity here. I included extra heat training by wearing long sleeves.

7386920.description: Testing out the RunAmoc DASH Smooth on the track.  Four x 400m with jog 400 in between.  Splits: 1:20 / 1:21 / 1:20 / 1:19.

18689648.title: no sidewalks
18689648.description: Awesome run. Felt like a completely different runner today. Some of the things I have been doing lately:   1. Track training of long intervals at race pace, 2. doing my Achilles tendon therapy consistently, 3. improving my running form (mostly arm swing),  4. consuming bone broth and whole foods,  5. sleeping!   The bloody awesome weather certainly helps (temps in the high 50s this morning!).  Broke 100 miles in my Merrell Trail Gloves and they are still in great shape.

20856357.title: mile trail repeats
20856357.description: Heart rate and breathing were up today, still recovering from being sick I guess. Decided to stop the workout and just put in some easy miles.

36491130.title: first Team Florida Track Club practice

34282988.description: Averaged 6:50 pace for the last 4. I guess that counts as a tempo.
34282988.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

18658007.title: Track workout 6x800m 6x1600m
18658007.description: Marathon training. Thanks Meredith for setting me on the proper pace for these!  Splits: 3:21, 3:18, 3:23, 3:18, 3:08, 3:10 (800m), 6:38, 6:42, 6:44, 6:21, 6:32, 6:18 (1600m)

30943894.title: fartleks
30943894.description: Hat and gloves kind of day. Included a couple of miles of fartleks. First run in Altra Torins (original) that I bought on closeout. Great shoe!

36041920.title: warm up and down at Rembert Farms

7929934.title: barefoot walk / easy run
7929934.description: Attempting to apply what I am learning from Barefoot Ken Bob's new book "Barefoot Running Step by Step" http://amzn.to/mvxwbq  I definitely have not been bending my knees enough and cushioned shoes killed my cadence.

24075208.title: good morning run
24075208.description: A nice solid run. I like my new Merrell Bare Access shoes.

2933176.title: Tried the huarache sandals again.
2933176.description: After doing 2.4 miles with my friend Matt, I felt like going a little bit more... but the bottoms of my feet were a little tender. Decided to give the huaraches another try.  They were fine until they rubbed a raw spot in between my toes.

26950517.description: Good to catch up with running friends and hear the tales of fabulous race performances, injury recoveries, heroic baby deliveries, and monsoon madness!
26950517.title: Lloyd Clarke Sunday Runday

27045026.description: Nice cold day for the Newnan's Lake 15k race. My fitness is about where I thought it was (coming back from the foot injury). Today's time was 4 minutes slower than last year which I'm ok with considering how undertrained I am (out of racing shape!). I have done no real speed since August and have averaged less than 10 miles per week since after the 50k in October. Great job to my compadres who I was unable to catch in the last couple miles despite my having a strong finish. Finish Time: 1:04:15.  Splits: 6:49, 7:03, 7:11, 7:16, 6:55, 6:47, 6:45, 6:52, 6:45, 1:52.
27045026.title: Newnan's Lake 15k race

2530176.title: I run faster in Nike Frees
2530176.description: After running in my RunAmocs, I ran exactly the same route in my Nike Frees.  Despite being hot and tired already, I easily knocked over a minute off each mile pace.  At this point I'm pretty well convinced that I run faster and with less effort in my Nikes than any of my minimalist shoes (or barefoot).

33912593.title: campus C loop
33912593.description: Felt terrible at first (full of hamburger and fries) but by the end was feeling really good!

36388112.title: new trail
36388112.description: Found a trail near my house I had never been on before. Legs felt heavy. Glutes not happy.

22076796.title: Home to Paynes Prairie La Chua Trail
22076796.description: Such a beautiful morning for a long run! Got lost a little bit which was ok because I ended up running all the way to the north side of Paynes Prairie and the La Chua trail which is definitely a first for me. The new park at the Railroad station on Depot Ave looks really nice. Came through campus on the way back. This was good scouting for future long runs if I ever decide to train for another marathon.

10925553.description: Short run on day before the half marathon.
10925553.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

13693834.description: Ran early this morning on greenway trails and road.  More protection than Moc3 and Altra Adams.  No squishy cushion to throw off my stride.  The stiffness I noticed when first picking them up did not bother me while running.  They were comfortable sockless at this easy pace and distance.  I love that the Sampson lacing keeps the shoe nice and secure on the foot... so many minimalist shoes leave the ankle area loose with useless velcro straps.  Sampsons are nice shoes!
13693834.title: First run in Altra Sampsons

30582775.description: Humid! Legs were sore and tired but felt good 40 minutes in.
30582775.title: recovery

6848294.title: no sidewalks
6848294.description: Morning run.  Longest ever! Did my long greeway out-and-back twice and then tagged on some more at the end.  Even though I ate my homeade energy bars and drank fluids the whole way, I was really dead by the end and afterwards my weight was the lowest recorded this century.  Temperature probably went up 20 degrees from the beginning to the end.  Treated myself to Five Guys (hamburger and fries) for lunch.  Splits (actual running) for each out or back (4.4 miles each): 41:59 / 40:07 / 40:02 / 44:36.  Last 2.6 miles in 31:45.  About 12 minutes of jog to my house, refuel, and bathroom stops.  The 3 hours 31 minutes was total clock time.

29838969.description: Total of 19 on the day. Naps are awesome, BTW.
29838969.title: Lloyd Clarke sunday runday

33245755.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
33245755.description: Nice morning run!  My VFF SeeYa LS are starting to tear in the upper near the pinky toe. It's a real drag to only get 200 miles out of a pair of FiveFingers.

30660658.description: 50 degrees at the start! Broke out the tights and long sleeves. Meant to make this an easy recovery run but pushed along for parts of it. Clear blue skies and slight breeze made this a beautiful run day. My new Altra 3-Sum shoes pass the long run test.
30660658.title: Coooool LSD

14151949.title: Newnans Lake Conservation Area North Tract trails
14151949.description: Don't run the North Tract trails, at least from the west side parking area (off HWY 26). I had the printed map with me, didn't help. I wanted to run the Yellow loop. I think the map is downright wrong. Also, a Blue trail isn't even on the map but I somehow ended up on it.  Eventually turned around in frustration on two different occasions as the trail seemed to just stop or at least wasn't marked well enough to continue.  I found my way out and back to the car with some difficulty.

32169892.description: Terrible sick week, finally maybe starting to feel a little better.
32169892.title: neighborhood

35340868.title: hill sprints x 8
35340868.description: Monday hill sprints. Still not feeling great but hill sprints were better than last week.

17950831.description:
I was hoping to do 6 reps but wasn't quite there today.  400m recovery in between. Splits: 6:25, 6:19, 6:18, 6:08, 6:02
Meredith D. - thanks for pulling us through the workout today.
17950831.title: Track workout 5 x 1600m

15977307.title: The Daily plus three hill repeats

31533591.description: First run in Skins A200 compression tights. These will probably only come out on cold and dark situations. They are a bit more revealing than true running tights and I had to keep pulling them up for the first half of the run (the waist kept riding down).  However, they kept me quite comfortable, not too hot or cold, on this morning in the low 40s. Generally felt good this morning.
31533591.title: first run in Skins compression tights

2805300.description: I was just going to do a nice, easy morning run... but then two shod runners turned onto the trail at the same time as me.  The guy gave some neighborly advice: "Don't stub your toe on a tree root."  The female runner said "We're just jealous."   She actually had a nice midfoot strike, even though she was wearing marshmallow shoes.  I hung in behind them for a while, and when I turned onto 8th Ave I just started cruising (the other runners had stopped to rest)... and kept cruising... and kept cruising.  Pretty sure this is my fastest barefoot run yet.  There were quite a few people out today, so I contributed some good barefoot exposure to the world.  My leg muscles were "twitchy" afterwards.
2805300.title: Fast barefoot run

35473418.title: hill sprints
35473418.description: 10 x hill sprints after easy run

14529591.title: Brywood hills
14529591.description: Hills in the heat.  I wore my Altra Sampsons and again they seemed to aggravate my Achilles tendon which is a real bummer considering how much I like the shoes otherwise.

32357556.title: incline repeats x 5
32357556.description: Incline repeats .7 miles each on SW 2nd Ave near the golf course (NW 34th St. to Village Dr.).  Pretty much full recovery in between (jog back to start). Cranked it down on the last few. Splits: 4:39, 4:37, 4:17, 4:09, 4:03

35448963.title: noonday warm run on campus
35448963.description: Perceived effort was high due to the noonday heat. Last 3 miles at just over 7 minute per mile pace.

29056570.description: Tired legs and some blisters from yesterday's run in the rain.
29056570.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

36595628.title: coolio morning
36595628.description: Ran to the breakfast burrito place. :)

14917897.title: The Daily
14917897.description: I wear my VFF every once in a while to remind me of how much I hate them. In truth I hate that they rub holes in my skin, otherwise I would wear them more.

30804634.description: Great trail run at San Felasco. Crossed the wilderness area to find trails with as much elevation change as possible. Ran Hidden Rise and Hidden Pond among others. The GPS in my phone lost some of distance in the twisty single track sections. My NB MT00 shoes are starting to show some tearing in the uppers (at over 300 miles). Didn't have the nerve to eat my EPIC Bison bar while running but did chow down on it immediately after... delicious!
30804634.title: San Felasco trails

24743986.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

10539328.title: perfect running night ruined by the devil
10539328.description: Temps in the 50s made for a potentially perfect run. Wore my MWU3. I stopped wearing them last year since I wanted to save them for fast races. Tonight I wanted to get a good test run in them before the upcoming half marathon. Started off feeling great but after about 2 miles I began feeling pains in strange places like my calf, knees, glute/hip. Also had some serious pain in my achilles tendon for a bit. I was moving well without much effort and feeling good but I had to stop because I felt like I was on the edge of an injury. Pretty pissed I had to cut the run short. Raised heels are evil. I'm likely going 100 percent Zero Drop from now on.

18303068.title: hard effort long run
18303068.description: Perceived effort was pretty high, still a little sore and tired from yesterday's race. Just kept the pace at a level to keep my breathing high. This was a fasted run, only had water. Training the fat burning and glycogen conservation mechanisms. The first 6 miles averaged 8:25 pace.

13752402.title: Swamp stadium stairs
13752402.description: 8 x stadium stairs with no rest.  Hopefully I'll recover a little faster than last week.  Altra Sampsons let me feel a nice firm platform on every stair.

14840800.title: no sidewalks
14840800.description: Dear Moccasins, oh how I missed thee. Very Hot Day. Lost some time at the intersections waiting for 5 o'clock traffic and to refill my water bottle. The first real run in my Moc3s for a long time. A nice run.

5480297.title: RunAmocs on San Felasco trails
5480297.description: Two hammock cutoff loops.  The RunAmocs felt great.  Really happy I can run in them now that my technique has changed (no longer driving my foot into the front of the shoe).

28099798.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
28099798.description: Hat and gloves. Refining some form issues.

30756770.title: lunch time run
30756770.description: Now over 100 miles on my Altra The One shoes. Showing some wear on the outsole, but otherwise look to be barely used.

31395278.title: Hocking State Forest and Buckeye Trail
31395278.description: Trail running the Ohio Buckeye Trail through Hocking State Forest. Parked at Old Man's Cave and ran north to the Climbing and Repelling area, then back south past Cedar Falls and the big climb to the firetower. I think I am fighting a bug so decided not to run all the way to Ash Cave. Ended up hiking some of the steep hills.

31250609.title: San Felasco trails
31250609.description: A run with Dan Clark is always a good workout. San Felasco trails were covered in leaves. Took a good spill on a hidden root with less than a mile to go.

31002047.title: Nice morning
31002047.description: Bumped into Matthew H. shortly into my run so ran with him on the Five Points Half course. Nice conversational pace. Longer than I planned to run but no harm in getting extra miles during my last big week before taper.

17033336.description: Great trail run in San Felasco with Dan C., Meredith, and Stephanie. Way faster than I normally run my long runs so I got a *great* workout today. Couldn't have done this alone, so thanks guys! One water stop in the middle and no refuel, so this should have been a good fat burning day. I'm really happy with the Merrell Trail Gloves.
17033336.title: San Felasco trails

30328474.title: San Felasco double trail tempo
30328474.description: Great day for tempo run on the trails of San Felasco. As soon as I set off a light rain started and kept me cool the entire day. Ran a double tempo run with about 12 minutes recovery in between (Splits: 20:05, 19:17). I modified my normal route slightly and didn't take the grassy side trail into the woods since it hasn't been mowed in a while (tall wet grass). The main trail that is normally softy sandy was in good shape due to the rains. Started the day with tired and sore legs from the hard running earlier in the week. I got a little over 50 minutes warmup on my usual route before starting the tempo. Feeling very fit!

23594303.description: Legs were sore and tired this morning.
23594303.title: early morning run

18354027.description: Improved my 400m time by 2 seconds from last week. Today: 67 seconds. Took a while to recover my breathing.
18354027.title: Track time trial 400m

33012930.description: End of a long week, over 50 miles.
33012930.title: no sidewalks

5925269.title: barefoot last mile
5925269.description: Carrying my NB Minimus Road after taking them off in frustration.

17833525.title: morning run with Diane's group
17833525.description: This was the first time I ran with Diane's group. Huge turnout today, conversational pace. Added on a little extra by running to/from the group start. We did a rolling hills route along 23rd Ave and 39th Ave.

18932138.title: San Felasco outer loop
18932138.description: Nice morning run at San Felasco with Dan C. and Brian. Muscles and legs started to complain towards the end and my breathing rate ramped up so I settled for one loop. The pace felt brisk, I think it was good not to push too far after last weekend's 25-miler. Muscle microtears be gone!

25266895.description: Took the extra long way to the track this morning to get more miles.
25266895.title: miles

33273942.description: 1 mile with 8 x 60m sprints on the straights. Track was baking.
33273942.title: short sprints 60m on track

3728216.description: Trying out the new trail shoes.
3728216.title: Greenway trails near home

32045016.description: Halfway through my run I crossed paths with John and Meredith so I ended up running with them for a while. Good to catch up. Cold and some light rain.
32045016.title: run with friends

14883980.title: barefoot in the heat
14883980.description: The sidewalk along 34th street north of 39th ave is nice smooth white concrete... relatively cool even in the full afternoon sun and great for barefoot running. Very hot at 3pm and 90 degrees. I'm getting a good tan though.

2082456.description: Ran by myself so I could work on form.  I had to try out my new RunAmocs!  I like them a lot.  Seems like they are a little bit small (my toes end up pushing on the front inside of the moccasin) even though the Soft Star web site says to go smaller if between sizes (I wear size 9 1/2, ordered size 9).  The longest part of the shoe seems too close to the middle of the shoe, rather than offset in front of the big toe.  Also, the top of the shoe stretches over the big toe like a tent (as if there is not enough internal height). Not sure if a larger size would fix these issues or maybe just have to run in them more than once.
2082456.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway

21523896.description: A great day for the Trail of Payne 10k! It was nice to finish in the overall awards (3rd) with a new age group PR of 38:56. This is almost 50 seconds faster than November's Turkey Trot even though today's run was a much tougher course (more sugar sand). The new running technique is working, I definitely felt like I was racing today. Wore my super light NB Minimus MT00 trail shoes, they are da bomb for racing. Mile splits: 6:12, 6:18, 6:24, 6:25, 6:18, 6:10
21523896.title: Trail of Payne 10k race

19626887.description: Last track workout before the marathon. Nice and easy 6x400m. Splits: 1:33, 1:35, 1:31, 1:29, 1:36, 1:29
19626887.title: track workout

36525410.title: campus
36525410.description: Piriformis had me limping this morning but by the time I started running - no issue. Quads are damn sore though.

34321917.description: Great day for the Lloyd Clarke Sports Turkey Trot 10k race. Huge turnout, nice event. I ran a decent race, brought home an age group win in 38:54. Splits: 5:57, 6:09, 6:23, 6:24, 6:19, 6:28, 1:13
34321917.title: Turkey Trot 10k

4243955.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
4243955.description: Have some nagging sorenesses but feels good to run fast.  I think the slight slope of the sidewalks is affecting my hips... I need to remember to go counter-clockwise on my loop routes for a few weeks.

10310983.title: Rain Run
10310983.description: Nice easy recovery run/walk in the rain.  I like running in the rain and it has been a long time.  My legs were very crampy after yesterday's race, wanted to get them moving.  I was surprised that my Achilles Tendon didn't bother me at all when I stepped out of bed this morning!

24963753.title: San Felasco trails south and north sides
24963753.description: Ran from the south side of San Felasco to the north side and back. Saw lots of wildlife including feral pigs (with baby piggies!), a gray fox, owl, hawk, and lots of deer. The run included the Sanchez horse trail and Conquistador bike trail. Conquistador is awesome with lots of ups and downs. Refilled water at the north entrance. I am finally starting to know my way around up there! I did take a map with me though (and needed it!). Tested my 50k fueling / fluid plan.

24136975.description: Less sleep and hard workouts are catching up with me.
24136975.title: 8th Ave short flat

5349762.description: I really like the hammock cutoff loop due to the concentration of hilly terrain.
5349762.title: San Felasco Hammock Cutoff - lap 1

33776711.title: DNA bridge bike path
33776711.description: First run after having the pain in my right foot at the cuboid bone checked out. Foot felt ok. Instructions were that it is ok to run as long as I am not favoring it or altering my gait. Some soreness came back shortly after the run, so I will continue to take it easy.

30495393.description: Ran before and after and while spectating at the Mt. Dew Invitational. Some FAST runners there today (the men's winner went through the first mile in 4:30ish). First run in new shoes, Altra 3-Sum. Like them a lot.
30495393.title: Spectating XC meet

20736519.description: Just some easy striding and captured it on video.
20736519.title: Greenway with video camera

34956820.title: Sweetwater Preserve
34956820.description: Nice run from campus to Sweetwater Preserve and then on the trails.

35938820.description: Tough track workout on a humid morning. 6 x 1200m (400m rest). We ended up breaking into two sets so we could get water halfway through. Splits: 4:33, 4:33, 4:37, 4:30, 4:27, 4:21
35938820.title: Track workout - 6 x 1200m

19685861.description: Finished my first marathon yesterday! Had a great time with lots of running buddies around for support! My muscle cramps were so ludicrous that I could only laugh afterwards. I had never experienced the "full body cramp" before. Went through the first Half in 1:31. Tried to hang with a pack of people for as long as I could but eventually had to fall off the pace and when the cramps started at mile 20 I basically ran when I could and walked when I had to. Pretty clear my goal time was not realistic, but now I have a baseline if I ever want to run another marathon. Finish time 3:26:14 Splits: 14:04 (mile 2), 7:04, 6:51, 6:53, 6:41, 7:02, 6:56, 6:52, 6:56 (mile 10), 6:55, 7:06, 6:56, 6:54, 6:58, 6:58, 7:20, 7:34, 7:38, 7:53 (mile 20), 8:35, 9:46, 10:44, 11:30, 10:58, 12:59 (mile 26).  Inov-8 Bare-X 150 on my feet.
19685861.title: Jacksonville Bank Marathon

29486275.title: Cataloochee Divide Trail
29486275.description: Cataloochee Divide Trail from the trailhead at Cove Creek Road to Purchase Gap. This trail runs near the park boundary inside the Great Smoky Mountains National Park. Elevation at the start was 4050 feet. The highest point was 4950 feet. Really nice single track running with lots of ups and downs. Would love to spend a week camping in the Cataloochee Valley and exploring all of the surrounding trails.

2351035.title: Testing my new Deuter backpack.
2351035.description: Run / walk in the dark in the rain in my VFF Bikilas.  I tested my new Deuter Race EXP backpack crammed full of stuff.  I think it will work for commuting.

35621592.description: Florida Track Club Twilight Track Meet - 1500m. Finished in 4:48. Legs were still feeling last week's track workout in the way up upper hamstrings. On 5 minute mile pace for the first few laps but fell off hard. Splits: 52 (first 300m), 1:14, 1:18, 1:20. Target was 1:14 per lap, 55 for the first 300m, so a little fast at the start. Official (hand-timed) results had me at 4:45, pretty big difference from my watch.
35621592.title: Track meet - 1500m race

5273569.description: fartlek x 2.  The new hip position / posture is almost starting to feel natural.  Feet were in good enough shape to wear VFF.
5273569.title: 8th Ave short flat

21655050.title: The Daily
21655050.description: Threw in a couple hard hill repeats at the end.

30241315.title: warm up and down
30241315.description: On the hilly XC course at Rembert Farms.

24625097.description: Double layers on bottom and top (thermal under layer and fleece jacket).  Hat and gloves. Body wanted to shut down at 28 minutes.  Went a little less than planned, but don't care.  Now I sit outside (still in the heat) and let the body cool itself down. Feels awful but I think it works well (like sauna training).
24625097.title: real heat training

9501882.description: I was inspired after learning that one of my new coworkers runs barefoot.  Included twice over my favorite coaching surface.  A little too soon after dinner... This run fueled by Adams Rib Co.
9501882.title: barefoot four

19319267.title: early morning greenways
19319267.description: Busted out the hat and gloves this chilly morning.

2754528.description: This morning I ran with some people from my last job.  They are joggers.  They meet early to run together, put on their headphones, and then maybe or maybe not stick together.  I was confused by the whole thing.  I'm not sure I want to get up at 5:15am to run with people by myself.  Actually towards the end one of them took of their gear and we were able to talk at a conversational pace which was nice.
2754528.title: run with joggers

36311417.description: Oh my such a nice cool morning. Track workout - 4 x 400m, 4 x 200m (200m recoveries) fast and smooth. Felt pretty good. Splits: 1:14, 1:21, 1:17, 1:15. 35, 34, 35, 33
36311417.title: Track workout - 4 x 400m, 4 x 200m

15661786.description: Time includes stadium stairs. Rained the whole time.
15661786.title: to the stadium and back

24328564.description: Legs a tiny bit sore and tired from yesterday stadium stairs, but "normal" runs feel like they take so much less effort now.  Passed 400 miles in my Altra Instincts.
24328564.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

5386484.description: Longest run for me in a long time.  Hopefully increasing my distance this week without causing any injuries. Last week I ran hard (intensity increase) so this week will be all easy runs.  I swear it got colder during this run... the cold, dank fog came after me.  Fueled by large portions of Ropa Vieja and mojo rice plus the Valentine's Day cookies I should not have eaten right before bed.

35610449.description: Sore and stiff at first. Loosened up a bit and felt pretty good.
35610449.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

34790945.description: Wanted a little more volume so pre-pended a 1600m on the front of the track workout. 1600m in 5:47 followed by 14 x 400m with mostly 200m rest (400m rest between sets): 1:18, 1:21, 1:20, 1:21, 1:22. 1:21, 1:20, 1:22,1:23. 1:23, 1:23, 1:25, 1:23, 1:24. Had some ouchy spots in foot and upper outside hamstrings, lower glute, had to take care.
34790945.title: Track workout 1 x 1600m, 14 x 400m

15661800.description: 4 x stadium stairs, ran as easy as possible.
15661800.title: four stadium stairs

3207135.title: Tempo run
3207135.description: Tempo run on the way back.  16th Ave got very dark on the last stretch from 34th St. so I had to slow down in the pitch black.  My lungs are my weak link right now.

13383617.title: cool night Moc3
13383617.description: Saved the hilly parts for last.

14688324.description: I've had a knot in my neck and shoulder for the last week... combined with being on-call, I didn't get much running in.  Glad to get in a barefoot run. The movement seemed to loosen up the muscles.  Ate poorly all week... lots of carbs and sugar.  Felt crummy because of it.  Hopefully I can put some actual miles in soon and make better food choices.
14688324.title: The Daily

22225155.description: After the race, I did some warm down and kept going a bit to try and keep warm on this cold, wet day.
22225155.title: keeping warm

12011610.title: Nice cool evening
12011610.description: Crashed and burned pretty hard on the last two miles, but glad I got in some good distance tonight with such perfect weather.

34005061.title: Alachua Lake Half Marathon race
34005061.description: Alachua Lake Half Marathon race on the Hawthorne trail. Another great Lloyd Clarke Sports event. I was 3rd overall and took home the Masters win. Felt pretty good and shows that my fitness is coming along, although not where I was last year at this time. I was able to push down the pace over the last few miles despite the hills. Finish time: 1:25:51. Splits: 6:29, 6:24, 6:37, 6:50, 6:28, 6:28, 6:33, 6:39, 6:37, 6:38, 6:33, 6:25, 6:21, 0:39

27453373.description: Stride straights jog turns for 1 mile.
27453373.title: track strides

5713402.title: huaraches and toe socks don't mix
5713402.description: Tried wearing sandals plus Injinji toe socks. Some people swear by it.  I took the socks off after about a half mile, they kept slipping around on the surface of the sandal.  Sock-free, I paid attention to the laces on the top of my foot, no rubbing issues today.  Huaraches are not my favorite footwear.

22184961.description: Included three laps on the track barefoot.
22184961.title: warm up and down

4450808.title: Warm enough to run barefoot!
4450808.description: It seems best for me to work on form issues without shoes on.  Pushing the hips forward / out plus keeping my trailing foot closer to the ground (instead of coming up so far under my butt) seems to be working... my front foot lands more under me than in front of me and it is way easier to maintain 180 cadence.  It also makes it hard to run slow.  :)   It *will* be nice when the sidewalks are free of acorns, nut shells, and other fall debris.

29211800.title: Track meet 1500m
29211800.description: Track meet at Cone Park. 1500m in 4:46.

18492370.description: Ran to Morningside and then 2x blue loop. Not sure why these mid-day runs have been sucking so hard. Not enough sleep? Still depleted from weekend long run?
18492370.title: Work to Morningside Nature Center

4738350.title: San Felasco hammock cutoff
4738350.description: Not sure the time is right... still figuring out my new watch.  Fizzled hard on this one, probably due to my attempt at cutting back on food intake yesterday.

31523814.description: Included half mile of sprint the straights on the track. Topo ST sticky rubber grabs the track well. Also nice for running sockless.
31523814.title: campus in Topo ST

20596309.title: cold morning warm up and down
20596309.description: Still felt good enough after the track workout and stadium stairs to push the pace a little on the way home.

4609037.description: Beautiful day. The temperature warmed up very fast (it was over 70 degrees by the time I was finished).  I saw a bobcat in the wild!  I followed him down the trail for a while before he noticed me (probably 20 feet away).  First long run with the chest strap on the heart rate monitor.  Works great.  I'm still learning what I need to do to get the information out of it afterwards though.  Was gonna run longer today but my form started to deteriorate so I called it quits.
4609037.title: San Felasco outer loop

30089224.title: Campus and steep hill sprints x 4
30089224.description: A few pains here and there including in my knees which hasn't happened in a long time. Last week I did 40 miles which is my highest mileage since April.  I turned 40 years old last week, too. Warm and humid today (got rained on and then the sun came out), only did 4 x steep hill sprints.

34628578.description: Ran gate to gate by way of Yellow trail to get more hills. Looks like this adds 2.5 miles each way over blue shortest route. I cut the end (came back blue/yellow) and had to walk / jog the last few miles so I got 20.5 instead of 23. Still a big day and over 32 for the weekend with this on top of tired legs from yesterday's workout.
34628578.title: San Felasco hilly long run

33917327.title: warm up and down to track

28234167.description: Sprints on the beach (up-slope from the waterline).
28234167.title: Beach

33901786.description: 2 x 4.58 mile tempo run with a little less than 4:30 active recovery in between to get some water. Very warm and humid this morning. First segment 33:49 (7:23 pace), Second segment 32:54 (7:11 pace).
33901786.title: tempo 2 x 4.58 miles

4802884.description: test to see how mileage shows up in challenges
4802884.title: nowhere fast

35500410.description: Working on some gait issues. Felt phenomenal during the middle section.
35500410.title: Bacon Strip 11

29146275.description: Tempo for 20:45. About a minute slower than last time. Very warm today and my stomach was recked this morning.
29146275.title: Trail Tempo

9659069.description: A nice cool night. My Moc3s were fine, this time I wore Injinji toe socks to prevent blisters between my toes.  Haven't run anything near this far since May.  I needed this.
9659069.title: long beautiful night run in Moc3

36636776.title: greenways
36636776.description: Actually felt very good this morning! Crossed paths with Coach Enoch so we ran together for a bit.

3458006.description: Beautiful sunrise this morning. Some people never see those. Ran 4 x Hammock Cutoff loop so had lots of hills.  The last loop was really tough physically and mentally, had trouble picking up the legs. Matt C. was supposed to come out but bailed due to fear of muddy trails.  Larabar + NUUN worked great. I ate two bars total and had two water bottles with NUUN spaced out over the run and never felt any stomach discomfort.  Started getting a knot/cramp in my quad during lap 2 (before Larabar and NUUN). Fueled up for lap 3 and the knot went away.  I think this is my longest run ever in my whole life (even going back to college XC days) and I did it barefoot.  Tired but happy, I feel prepared for what comes next.
3458006.title: Long barefoot trail run at San Felasco (Millhopper Rd)

35243079.description: Slept in today so skipped the trails. Put in a good effort long run. Last five at 7 minute pace.
35243079.title: VFF long run

32949682.title: no sidewalks
32949682.description: Wore long sleeves. It heated up a lot towards the end. Included a couple long fartleks at moderate pace: 4:04, 4:14

28321058.title: San Felasco trails tempo run
28321058.description: Tempo runs have been conspicuously missing from my training over the last three years. I am going to try including Tempos into my training from now on. San Felasco trails - time between signs Hammock Cutoff to Sand Hill Cutoff 10:22. 19:52 total.

30474242.description: Track days make me feel old. Started on target pace for the first interval but slowed for the rest and then completely ran out of breath by the last one. A little disappointing but I could tell going in that my leg muscles were still recovering from previous work. Less than 2 minutes rest between each. Splits: 3:29, 3:37, 3:38, 3:40, 3:52
30474242.title: Track 5 x 1000m

7431862.description: It was pretty cool to be lined up at the starting line behind / beside elite runners.  Unfortunately, this pulled me along to a first mile that was faster than planned. The race was hot and painful and a big mental challenge.  Happy with the results.  First in my age group.  The course was very well-marked, a nice venue.
7431862.title: Freedom 8k Inaugural race in Green Cove Springs

2713547.description: Awesome trail run in San Felasco with Cathy B.  It was nice to be able to draft off an experienced trail runner and not worry about getting lost in the miles and miles of trails at the Preserve.  Wildlife included some deer, an owl, and a barefoot runner.  This was a big jump in distance for me and I was definitely tired by the end.  Overall a great day.
2713547.title: San Felasco Preserve off 441

9728016.title: moc3 long run
9728016.description: Finally got back up over 30 miles per week.

28286922.description: Much cooler than previous years for the LGAA 5k race. Good food provided afterwards. Some mix-ups in the results, but I think I won my age group (and thus got a cupcake!) and was on the winning team for Youth Combine.
28286922.title: LGAA 5k race

28496952.description: Started off with 6 x steep hill sprints on my way to the track. Did a "checkpoint" workout for the 5k, which is 5 x 1000m with 1 min rest in between.  I still have plenty of work to do. Splits (rest): 3:33 (1:07), 3:37 (1:08), 3:44 (1:10), 3:48 (1:08), 3:44
28496952.title: Track 5 x 1000m

27875203.title: Track 6 x 800m
27875203.description: First some strides up to full speed, then 6 x 800m on the track. Planned for 2:50 per rep with around 2 minutes recovery. Splits: 2:44, 2:47, 2:48, 2:50, 2:47, 2:48

17538991.description: Nice morning trail run with Stephanie and Meredith. Everyone else must have been sleeping in (or having van trouble... we missed you Dan C.!). Finished good and tired.
17538991.title: San Felasco long run

24557848.description: Sore and stiff at the beginning, especially my Achilles tendons.
24557848.title: morning

36648512.description: Track workout 2 x 400m, 8 x 200m with equal distance rest to each rep. 400m splits: 1:26, 1:25.  200m splits: 39, 38, 37, 37, 38, 37, 36, 35
36648512.title: Track workout 2 x 400m, 8 x 200m

32487175.description: Power went out last night so I was up in the middle of the night a few times, not feeling well-rested this morning. Track workout 10 x 300m and 2 x1000m. Approx 1:30 rest between each rep with a longer break before the 1000s. Splits: 53, 55, 53, 52, 53, 54, 53, 54, 54, 53, 3:43, 3:40
32487175.title: Track 10 x 300m and 2 x 1000m

35871121.description: First run in new VFF V-Run. I used my "Free Pair of Shoes" gift certificate / spoils from winning Masters division in a race last year. The upper of these shoes are made almost entirely of stretchy material. The heel area is a little more loose than I like but otherwise they feel fine.
35871121.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

35419104.description: Some easy running and also video capture with Richard G. Nice form capture, including slow motion: https://youtu.be/uSy-fq-rZJ0
35419104.title: video capture of strides on track

17607608.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
17607608.description: A little stiffness in the Achilles tendons but otherwise ok. I neglected them over the last couple of days since I was taking recovery days. Bad idea. The run felt nice and easy.

16795067.title: morning
16795067.description: Ankles and Achilles were sore and tight this morning. Took it easy.

35078146.description: Track workout 12 x 200m @ 3k pace turned into 12 x 200m "Quick but Smooth" which we ended up running way faster than expected. Felt very quick! I modified the workout half-way, turning it into 2 sets of 6 x 200m, increasing the recovery to 400m between the sets. This also let us run fast on both halves of the track. Splits: 33, 34, 34, 33, 34, 33. 34, 34, 34, 33, 34, 32. (Rest 1:30 between reps, 3:00 between sets).
35078146.title: Track 12 x 200m

32574977.title: no sidewalks
32574977.description: I don't think it was humid enough this morning. Greenways were surprisingly not muddy considering the rain we had last night.

4386199.title: First run back after being sick
4386199.description: My sinus issue will drag on for the next few weeks, but overall feeling good enough to run again.  All of my joints and connective tissue were very glad to have a week off anyway.

14151633.description: Hatchet Creek Tract is part of the Newnans Lake Conservation Area (north side of HWY 26). I had some free time today for a second run, decided to go exploring since I have never run there before.  There are no facilities despite what is shown on the map.  Had a nice strong breeze the whole time bringing in cloud cover. I think it would have been hot and miserable otherwise. The trails are nice and wide (and flat), this might make a good location for a group trail run. There is of course some sugar sand but really not bad, most trails are covered in leaves or pine needles or planted in grass. The Yellow loop is a convenient 5k. Taking a map along was very helpful, I would have had trouble without it.  Wore my NB MT00 sockless, had no issues.  Lesson of the day: Top of your water bottle when you get the chance.  I drank some of mine on the way there and didn't refill from my jug before leaving my car.
14151633.title: Hatchet Creek Tract trails

21006939.description: Seems like a while since I took a genuinely "easy" effort run, going extra slow on purpose. My legs are still pretty sore from the weekend races. I think this is what I needed today. Pace is actually faster than I thought it would be. Mentally I'm a bit frustrated with my current performance plateau.
21006939.title: Waldo Road Greenway LSD

30241421.description: Cross Country Challenge 5k race at Rembert Farms. Tough course! Significant hills! Really nice event, I hope there are more races up there in the future. Got to run the big hills twice. Won my age group. Splits: 6:09, 6:42, 7:22
30241421.title: Cross Country Challenge 5k race

29367952.description: Running off last night's pizza and 3 Skull Splitter Orkney Ales. There were loads of runners out this morning, moving in droves...
29367952.title: morning

2616574.description: I wanted to go exploring and find some new trails close to home.  It turns out that the nature trails at this city park are very short.  However, there are lots of places to run nearby including Devil's Millhopper so I managed to get over 5 miles in.  It was HOT and this was my first run carrying a water bottle.

35364717.title: power line roads
35364717.description: Warm evening run with Richard. Explored some powerline roads near his house.

33665121.title: campus C loop
33665121.description: Stomach still full of lunch (Reggae Shack oxtail goodness) and legs tired from yesterday.

17206058.title: 8th Ave short flat
17206058.description: Barefoot during a rain shower. Still feeling Thursday's speed workout.

22508525.description: Really nice damp cool evening.  Too bad my VFF tore holes in my feet. Surged the hills on the way back into a gusty headwind.
22508525.title: Santa Fe water stop out-and-back

33672306.description: Saw a cute little baby deer and its momma... just barely avoid getting hit by a car.
33672306.title: lunchy longish run

35331975.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

4730938.title: nice run in VFF
4730938.description: Rolled out of bed after a nap and hit the greenway  I feel like the strengthening work is paying off.  Tempo run in the middle felt fast and easy.

20597290.description: Stole this workout from Dan Clark's training log.  6 x 800m continuous, alternating tempos between moderate and hard. This is a great workout since it forces the body to recover while still running at a pretty good pace. Splits:  3:39, 3:00, 3:28, 2:53, 3:29, 2:46
20597290.title: Track workout 6 x 800m

22813389.description: Still sick as a dog and having a horrific on-call rotation. This is about all I could muster.
22813389.title: barefoot

33477889.description: Nice light rain at the beginning that turned into steamy run. Included some sightseeing along Lake Alice. Saw BIG fish.
33477889.title: campus A loop

18446809.title: 2x long greenway route
18446809.description: Actually felt really good at the start since it was nice and cool. It started to heat up around 10am which definitely affected the back half of my run. Experimenting with marathon fuels, this morning was honey + blackstrap molasses which worked great. I was moving well and feeling good. Unfortunately the "sugar" was all gone by the 2nd lap and I crashed hard shortly after 2 hours. It seems like once I start taking sweets I will have to keep it going in. I will have to ponder this since most of my morning runs are in the fasted state and I don't normally bonk that hard.

33006226.description: San Felasco trails - out and back to picnic table at Turkey Creek. Saw my first in-the-wild coral snake. "Red on yellow, kill a fellow..."
33006226.title: San Felasco trails - out and back Turkey Creek picnic table

34180287.title: Arlington Custis Trail and Potomac Heritage Trail
34180287.description: Cold and foggy... PERFECT for running! The Custis bike path is amazingly well-marked, very impressive. Found some chunky rocky parts on the Potomac Heritage Trail.  Avg. pace is slow because I stopped to take some pictures.

35899788.description: A deliberately truly easy no effort run.
35899788.title: campus A loop

22368655.description: Nice trail run with Dan C.  Hope to make this Saturday morning trail run a regular thing.
22368655.title: San Felasco Trails

36645130.title: Round Knob x 2 plus HS XC course

2069257.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
2069257.description: Ran the whole thing in my Nike Frees.  Felt great until my calf went out and I had to gimp the last little bit.

35798147.title: tempo in heat
