35798147.description: Solid warmup then pushed the pace until I overheated and had to ease back.

4967573.description: I was pleasantly surprised that I didn't have any of the "big toe pressure" issues that I used to get in my RunAmoc moccasins.  My conversion from forefoot to midfoot apparently keeps my toe from jamming up in the front of the moc.  I also wore them much looser around the ankle and this was not a problem, either. Traction was good even on wet boardwalk. They were plenty warm this morning (with socks) and felt great all around.
4967573.title: Gave the RunAmocs another try

14419290.title: very long run
14419290.description: Feet are in fine shape thanks to my Altra Instincts. Ran out of fuel at the end.

13991097.description: This morning jog seems to be doing good things for my sore Achilles tendons.
13991097.title: The Daily

6626945.title: Run run run til the sun comes up...
6626945.description: Saw coyote or grey fox in Cofrin Nature Park.

18389379.title: Track workout 4 x 1600m
18389379.description: I intended to do more reps at marathon pace, but woops ran the first mile too fast. Pacing is hard. I did 4 reps with less than 3 minutes rest in between by running my recovery lap faster than a jog. Looking forward to having my workout buddies back on the track. Splits: 5:47, 6:03, 6:09, 5:58.

4000095.description: Started out as a short run to get the kinks out.  Once I got warmed up I decided to go longer.
4000095.title: night run

31477807.title: recovery
31477807.description: A pain lingering in my right hip front (at the thigh muscle tendons).

29211805.title: Track meet 3000m
29211805.description: Track meet at Cone park. 3000m in 10:49.

35646080.description: Track 1 Mile time trial. Most of the group bailed this week so I was basically running a solo effort. It was warm and soupy. Finished with a disappointing 5:17. On the upside, my splits were consistent with "even pacing" and the last lap was strong (by comparison). Unfortunately, every lap was just 4 seconds too slow! Splits: 80, 78, 80, 77
35646080.title: Track - 1 Mile time trial

35478421.description: Track workout - 8 x 800m (200m rest between most reps).  Paced Richard G. through his workout first then added on two more. Very humid this morning. Splits: 3:24, 3:25, 3:20, 3:23, 3:19, 3:26, 2:56, 2:48.
35478421.title: Track - 8 x 800m

35281689.description: Hogtown 5k Beer Run. The accuracy of the course has been questionable in previous years so I didn't wear a watch and just raced. 3rd overall, got a gift certificate and a nice big beer mug. Free pizza and beer after, a nice event!
35281689.title: Hogtown 5k Beer Run

5883922.description: I was bad at dinner so this was to help burn off a huge pile of fish and chips (fried fish, onion rings, and french fries).  Decided to stay off concrete sidewalks and find some nice, quiet neighborhoods so I could run on the asphalt streets.
5883922.title: neighborhoods

13860321.description: Started with Brywood hills loop and then hit the greenways once the sun came up.  Stopped to listen to a flock of wild turkeys gobbling in the distance and later to watch a large owl (watching me).
13860321.title: recovery day

34374264.description: One of those rare almost effortless runs. Chilly evening with constant breeze was really nice. Earlier in the week I realized that I had lost some of my running efficiency. I am tweaking my form again and so far it is paying off.
34374264.title: cool evening

3961644.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
3961644.description: Shake-out run getting ready for Saturday.

3694083.title: 13th St to Brywood
3694083.description: Feet and achilles could be happier but nothing major to report.  Guess I was moving pretty fast.

5988347.description: Trail of Payne is an awesome trail race!  Great day!  Could not be happier!  Wanted to go out slow and run this as a progression.  We ended up just a little faster than I planned on the first mile, but we held this and increased pace through most of the splits.  Thanks Patrick Oscar B. for pulling me through to a great time and we had fun while doing it.  Splits were something like: 7:02/6:59/6:45/6:55/6:40/6:38/1:07.  Managed 2nd in my age group. Now, to ice my Achilles tendon area...
5988347.title: Trail of Payne 10k

7546091.title: no sidewalks
7546091.description: Wow bleh!  Creaky in the ankles and many muscles are still sore from Friday's Core workout at GHFC, especially the glutes.  Did some walking.  Feet feeling odd, wonder if my shoes are starting to break down (my Altra Instincts have 230 miles on them).

35847232.description: Mild headache due to some beers yesterday, but felt better as went along and cranked down the pace into a progression run. Splits: 10:31, 9:25, 9:33, 8:01, 7:41, 7:36, 7:07, 7:01, 6:27.
35847232.title: progression

17791260.description: Track workout. 2x800m, 1x1600m, 2x800m, 1x1600m with 400m recovery in between.  Splits: 2:51, 2:49 (800m), 5:45 (1600m), 2:53, 2:50 (800m), 5:44 (1600m). The last one was tough.
17791260.title: Track workout

35212908.title: Track workout 2 sets 5 x 500m
35212908.description: Tough workout! Track - 2 sets of 5 x 500m @ 3k pace (300m recovery between reps, 700m recovery between sets). Splits: 1:37, 1:41, 1:42, 1:38, 1:38. 1:39, 1:39, 1:37, 1:35, 1:34

34925633.title: Five Points of Life Marathon
34925633.description: Cool morning but warmed up a lot towards the end of the Five Points of Life Marathon. Ran a PR, met the BQ standard, and earned 1st Masters overall. 6th place overall put me just outside of the overall cash prizes. Miles 24 onward were especially tough with a lot of full sun. Ran pretty even splits, avg. 7:14 for the first half, 7:26 for the second half, 7:20 overall.

2642461.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
2642461.description: Yeah... today probably should have been a rest day.  I worked late, so I ran later than usual but had no dinner before.  Do not start a run when your stomach is grumbling for food!  I was so out of Lift that I even let myself heel strike for portions of the run and also did some walking.

32438909.description: Great morning for the Flatwoods 5k race. Hard effort, raced with the pack as long as I could, didn't run with a watch. Just missed going under 18 minutes. My inov-8 Trailroc 235 shoes were perfect for the limerock road surface. Won my age group. Finish time: 18:01
32438909.title: Flatwoods 5k race

4438899.description: Using the new POSE-inspired form that my Physical Therapist wants me to try.  It apparently did not make me slower.
4438899.title: loop near West Side Park

32944424.description: 4 x hill repeats in the heat. Splits: 1:57, 1:50, 1:53, 1:47
32944424.title: one third mile hill repeats

35060529.title: GATE River Run 15k
35060529.description: Turned into a hot run at the GATE River Run 15k race. 1:00:54 is not a 15k PR, but did improve my time over last year by about a minute and a half. Finished considerably higher in the standings (156th out of 14398 total finishers, 6th in my age group out of 620). Last mile in 6:04. Splits: 6:18, 6:13, 6:26, 6:37, 6:33, ...

7679387.description: Short striders in various shoes while recording to a little 10 dollar digital video camera.  Good enough to notice a couple of things about my form.
7679387.title: Strides

36041998.description: 2016 XC 5k Challenge race at Rembert Farms. This year the course was single loop with a significant portion through the wooded area by the creek (which was dry). Some steep hills and some long gradual uphills made for a challenging course. 4th overall and felt like I had a solid run. Forgot my watch but the course had no mile markers anyway.
36041998.title: 2016 XC 5k Challenge race at Rembert Farms

17376195.title: Stadium stairs at The Swamp
17376195.description: I arrived before the sun rose above the rim of the stadium which was a nice change. Finished 10 x stairs in 28 minutes with just a little walk recovery in between each rep. Ran to the stadium and back from my house. All this before breakfast.

22225305.title: Fallen Heroes 5k
22225305.description: Cold. Rainy. AWESOME! Huge age group PR for me at the Fallen Heroes 5k with a finish time of something like 17:37. My mini-taper seems to have payed off. Brought home a nice bunch of gift cards since I won overall and they gave me age group winner, too.

4535202.description: Santa and family were good to me this year.  Received a bunch of running clothes and a stopwatch / heart rate monitor.  Had to try them out.
4535202.title: xmas day run

27270680.title: nasty cold rainy day
27270680.description: Tired legs!  I think I have my form dialed in for the race next weekend.

22143338.title: Waldo Rd to Sweetwater Preserve west trails
22143338.description: 3.4 miles to the trailhead from work. My first time on the West trails of Sweetwater Preserve, found some nice singletrack. Felt miserably hot out there today, hard to believe it's only the low 80s.

10704374.description: Gotta start eating better during the weekends.  Lower legs still not feeling happy.
10704374.title: Wandering and exploring

35705285.title: fitness pit in heat
35705285.description: Finished with lunch at Burrito Bros.

5818782.title: Puerto Rico!
5818782.description: Beach running in beautiful Puerto Rico!  The sand was really soft, running was difficult as my feet kind of sunk in with every step... it felt kind of like running through deep snow.  I think total mileage for the trip was around 6 miles.  Also did a lot of hiking in the El Yunque national rain forest in my 4mm cherry huarache sandals.  We didn't get above 700m (2300 feet) of elevation, but all of the trails were very steep down and up.

3287283.description: Definitely cooler tonight.  Achilles is still a long way from 100%.  Chased my daughter on her bike again, then ran some more after.  Since the students came back to Gainesville there is a *lot* more broken glass out there.  Leaves are starting to fall on the trails, obscuring the hazards.
3287283.title: more chasing training wheels

17011970.description: Ran in my Altra Provisions with the "stability wedge" installed.
17011970.title: The Daily

23817212.title: Brywood to 13th St
23817212.description: I was all sweaty and nasty from helping my neighbor split wood so I went for a run after.  Legs still sore from Sunday.  First run in Merrell Bare Access (got them at Ross for 40 bucks). They are very lightweight zero drop shoes. So far so good.

31782569.description: Took a few walk / jog breaks during the workday. Calves are sore, other kinks and quirks, whatever is going on with my ankle (pain and swelling just above the medial malleolus)... just tried to loosen up a bit today.
31782569.title: easy walk jog

19801479.description: Ran from Old Man's Cave to Cedar Falls to Ash Cave along the Buckeye Trail in the Hocking Hills.  How did I miss out on this during all those years living in Ohio?  Cold day (32 degrees), lots of icicles hanging from the rock formations. The section between Old Man's Cave and Cedar Falls is technical with rocks, roots, and stone stairways to navigate. I was glad to have my Altra Superiors. The section between Cedar Falls and Ash Cave is not technical but has some serious hills leading up to the fire tower.
19801479.title: Hocking Hills trail run

7523574.description: Jog to Gainesville Health and Fitness and back home.
7523574.title: GHFC round trip

15874490.description: A little Barefootery for Father's Day.
15874490.title: The Daily times two

32790379.description: stadium stairs. 6 x full, 6 x sprints on lower flight
32790379.title: stadium stairs

2112630.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
2112630.description: Ran most of this in my huarache sandals.  The last 3/4 mile barefoot.  Cadence Cadence Cadence!  Someone stopped me to chat because he had never seen anyone running in sandals before.

28601037.description: Fizzled. Cut the workout short. A month ago I added 3 new training elements (steep hill sprints, 1000m intervals, and tempo runs). This week probably should have been a recovery week if I were following a schedule. I felt tired most of this week and fell off pace quickly during the track workout. Adjustments: I am going to move my steep hill sprints their own day so they don't affect my specific training on track day. Will possibly take a recovery week. 6 steep hill sprints. 4 x 1000m, 1 x 400m. Splits (rest): 3:30 (1:40), 3:33 (2:48), 3:39 (3:14), 3:55 (3:17), 1:14 for 400m.
28601037.title: Track 1000m repeats and hill sprints

35841565.description: Started slow and stiff but ended up fartlek-style on the hills towards the end.
35841565.title: Farmhaven

31640035.description: Still nursing my left Achilles tendon flare up. On the upside... new trail shoes! First run in Altra Superior 2.0. Also new to me Altra The Lone Peak 1.5 that a friend gave me.  All goodness. So many shoes I had to "retire" some so dailymile would let me add the new ones.
31640035.gear:
Altra The Lone Peak 1.5
Altra Superior 2.0
31640035.title: easy greenways

36520506.title: team run with Rob
36520506.description: cold morning! Tired out by the end.

35421123.description: Legs were sore but enjoyed the run.
35421123.title: San Felasco trails

31903542.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
31903542.description: Injected moderate pace with easy effort in the middle (although it was only 8 min per mile).

26461723.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

3349717.title: San Felasco (Millhopper Rd)
3349717.description: Gluts were sore from Thursday hill workout.

24310791.title: Swamp stadium stairs
24310791.description: Full stairs bottom to top and back with no rest in between. Felt like I was going to pass out after the last one so I guess I pushed hard into oxygen debt. Finished 8 reps total, most reps under 1:50.

36258611.title: Stadium Stairs at Swamp
36258611.description: Stadiums. 2 x stairs, 2 x bleachers. Bleachers in 35 seconds.

23804509.title: woops
23804509.description: Got into this morning's run and realized that I had miscalculated the time I needed to get back to wake the kids up for their summer day camp. Had to book it home. Legs still very sore but did not feel like a hard effort even on the way back. Out and back splits: 27:16, 18:39

26875962.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

2881571.description: VFF Bikila seem to be nice for running in the rain on man-made surfaces. Felt weird today... breathing was not fast or hard at all but my heart rate seemed high.  Started getting a twinge in my arch after 4 miles, so stopped to walk. Took off the VFF and walked barefoot for a bit.

5698725.title: long night loop
5698725.description: Felt pretty crummy the whole way, although turned part of it into a tempo run... it is hard not to speed up running past campus and the bars on University Ave.  I've been behind on sleep, stressed, and eating like crap.  I was under-veggied, under-fruited, over-meated, and over-junk-fooded this week.  I think my body and glutes noticed that I've been skipping my PT and core strengthening lately.  On the bright side, I think all of the push-ups etc. are paying off... I'm pretty sure I received a cat call from a car full of college girls.

5349792.title: San Felasco Hammock Cutoff - lap 2
5349792.description: Pushed the second lap a little bit more.

35594410.title: greenways
35594410.description: Legs feeling tired and of course mid-afternoon heat and humidity. Love my TrailRocs!

19024020.title: Yasso 800s
19024020.description: Legs were still sore from Tuesday stadium stairs, especially calves and quads. I thought I'd try Yasso 800s for the first time today since I was working out solo. Didn't make it to 10 reps (I did 9 and had to quit). I can see how this workout can be used as a marathon predictor... it's all about glycogen depletion! Kept the 400m recovery laps faster than a jog, at around 2 minutes or less (8-minute pace for recovery). Splits (800m): 3:32, 3:16, 3:13, 3:07, 3:05, 3:10, 3:07, 3:15, 3:12.  Based on this workout my target marathon goal ought to be around 3 hours 15 minutes or better, and sub-3 hours is probably not realistic.

7239054.title: barefoot morning run
7239054.description: Just now getting a chance to log it in dailymile.

4423449.description: It was cold at 5am but at least there was very little wind.  Base layers people, base layers.

11697994.title: Barton Creek Greenbelt
11697994.description: A rocky trail worthy of my Altra Lone Peaks.  Really glad I had a rock plate.  Not exactly sure of the distance... the gps app on my phone quit tracking whenever I stopped to take a photo.  Survived with just carrying water but kinda wish I had packed some calories.  Fun day!

24310725.title: Swamp stadium Bull Gator statue roundtrip

3769624.description: I'm ready to retire my Nike Free Run+ shoes.  Shoes with elevated heels can suck it.
3769624.title: Out in Nike Frees

35727492.description: Easy and steep hill sprints x 10. On campus near the police station.
35727492.title: steep hill sprints x 10

3927449.title: Brywood to 13th St
3927449.description: This was supposed to a super slow easy run... but I found a rhythm and could not slow down.  Cool night temps are awesome. Today was the first day that I aggressively massaged my Achilles.  Seems to be helping.  I have a house full of shoes from Zappos and have to decide what shoes to wear for this weekend's half marathon.

7786591.title: University Ave 6mi loop
7786591.description: Ran in VFF, last 1.5 miles barefoot.  Nice cool breeze since thunderstorms are moving through this morning.  Had to stop and slow down when I felt a twinge in my way upper glute (almost on top on the way to my hip). After walking a bit I decided to take off the shoes and jog it in barefoot.

20362977.description: Good times in the forest as always.  Calves still sore from Thursday's track workout.
20362977.title: ACMF run

31077604.title: St. Augustine Half Marathon race
31077604.description: Beautiful morning for the St. Augustine Half Marathon race. Earned 4th overall, 1st in my Age Group, and best of all set a lifetime PR by over 2 minutes 20 seconds. Mile split times (some are double... I was busy racing for 3rd place and missed a few):  6:58, 12:30, 5:59, 6:32, 6:16, 6:21, 12:24, 6:29, 6:31, 6:36, 7:00

28796915.description: Easy barefoot. Included a mile around the track.  Over 350 barefoot miles total since I stared running in May 2010.
28796915.title: easy barefoot

5874915.title: easy barefoot
5874915.description: Working on foot pad development.  Makes a nice warmup before starting my Achilles tendon PT.

18455138.title: Lloyd Clarke Sports group run
18455138.description: Nice way to finish off a 50-mile week. The Lloyd Clarke Sports group is trying to meet every Sunday at 6pm.

29860263.title: Santa Fe water stop out-and-back
29860263.description: Running on tired legs is a good way to improve running efficiency... and boy were my legs tired! Good solid run.

30713144.description: Track workout 7 x 1200m with 400m (2:20-2:50) recovery. After the first two reps I thought I would only be able to do four total, my legs were still feeling tired from the weekend, but by the time I finished each recovery lap I was ready to go again and do another, and another, and another. A good confidence builder. Splits: 4:35, 4:33, 4:29, 4:36, 4:24, 4:29, 4:31 (6 minute per mile pace is 4:29)
30713144.title: Track workout 7 x 1200m

7849527.description: Turned into a walkfest.  Not sure if it's in my head or if my body really needs a break.  I intend to take a few weeks off.  I have never in my life trained consistently for an entire year, it is reasonable that the body needs some complete rest.
7849527.title: San Felasco 3x Hammock cutoff

13149192.description: Still having pain across the top of my right foot. Cut the run short.
13149192.title: cool barefoot morning

35967940.description: Gate to Gate by way of Conquistador. Had the trails almost entirely to myself. Rained or drizzled the whole time. Ran out of gas and walked towards the end. Salomon hydration vest worked well and coupled it with Nathan "Peak" waist hydration belt.
35967940.title: San Felasco trails in the rain

5551873.title: long night loop
5551873.description: Perfect evening for a run.  Wore my VFF.

16023686.title: 8th Ave short flat
16023686.description: Saw a *lot* of other runners out there today.

23302924.title: Track workout 4 x 800m
23302924.description: Ran what Bernd called a threshold workout. 4 x 800 with 100m recovery and we actually continued to chatter some during the workout. Tagged on a little extra mileage around the track at the end. Splits: 3:15, 3:16, 3:11, 3:08

2793205.description: Trail running is best.  Thanks Cathy!
2793205.title: San Felasco Preserve off 441

28826526.title: 8th Ave short flat
28826526.description: Felt good once I loosened up. Quads are still sore deep inside (probably why my last few speed sessions fizzled so badly) so I will continue to take it easy for a while.  Foot feeling good in my VFF. Gainesville summer track meet series starts in a couple of weeks.

36442967.title: Chattanooga Renaissance Park and River Walk
36442967.description: Chattanooga has some really nice areas near the river.

32466427.title: early morning
32466427.description: Wore long sleeves to keep my training in the uncomfortably warm zone. Tired.

19909423.title: Happy 2013
19909423.description: First run of the new year!  Making myself take it easy.

36302931.title: San Felasco trails
36302931.description: There are some trees down after Hurricane Matthew so I packed my folding saw and cleared some limbs while I ran. The saw fits great in the back pocket of my Salomon hydration vest. Still not feeling great overall, piriformis still bothering me, but I put in a few moderate effort miles towards the end. Cooler and dryer weather is amazing.

35732113.title: Track workout - 4 x 1200m
35732113.description: Track workout - 4 x 1200m (200m rest). Warm and steamy. Trying some new breathing technique (switching to a 2-1 pattern when I can no longer maintain a 3-2 pattern). Consistent splits: 4:14, 4:13, 4:14, 4:16

2555079.title: 5 miles in Nike Free Run+
2555079.description: Really tight at the beginning.  Had a few "Eureka" moments where the technique all came together and I was LIFTING instead of PUSHING and felt like I was floating along.  Now, if I can only transfer that over to my minimalist shoes...

2703169.title: 3mi barefoot
2703169.description: Went really slow trying not to aggravate the foot.  Wanted to get those healing juices flowing.   Icing now.  Made the mistake of wearing cotton thinking it was not yet very hot outside.

32586751.title: campus
32586751.description: Supposed to be taking it easy but I felt good. Didn't push above moderate effort.

21934557.description: Another perfect Florida morning for racing! It feels nice to WIN a race! The Flatwoods 5k is an all around great event held at the Austin Cary Forest. Finish time was 18:27 with Splits of 6:06, 6:00, 6:24 (last 1.1 mile).
21934557.title: Flatwoods 5k

30784920.description: Sooo cooooool... Breathing was easy and perceived effort was near zero. I wanted to go further or maybe do a tempo run but my hamstrings and quads are not recovered from previous workouts. I decided to hold off. The cool temps are going to stick around for a few days.
30784920.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

34019806.description: Wore long sleeves! Bumped into nice friends. Sore legs.
34019806.title: cool morning

27957034.description: Long warmup, half mile of strides, then 10 x 400m. Nailed the workout, targeting 5:20 mile pace (under 1:20 per quarter), no more than 2 minutes rest in between each rep. Splits: 1:19, 1:17, 1:19, 1:16, 1:18, 1:19, 1:15, 1:20, 1:18, 1:16
27957034.title: Track 10 x 400m

32314288.description: Great cool morning for the Trail of Payne 10k race! Good runners there today! Finished in 39:40. A tough month with allergies and sick and recovery from Five Points so a bit out of race shape. I feel good about my effort and I was able to fend someone off with a strong finish kick. Mental was there today. Over a minute faster than last year. Splits: 6:14, 6:16, 6:37, 6:34, 6:39, 6:22, 1:01
32314288.title: Trail of Payne 10k race

34212598.description: Track workout 4 x 100m, 4 x 200m, 4 x 300m, 3 x 400m. Bailed the second half of workout.
34212598.title: Track workout ladder

33060872.title: track workout 6 x 1000m in the heat
33060872.description: Scorcher of a track workout, and I'm not talking about my times. By the end, temp. was 93 degrees with "feels like" 98 degrees. Calves and quads were still sore from stairs 2 days ago. Combined with allergies and some personal stuff going on this week... well, not a great workout except for getting in some hard work in the heat. 6 x 1000m splits: 3:38, 3:52, 4:01, 4:20, 4:12, 4:08 with 1:30 - 3:00 rest / water break in between.

28626617.title: barefoot recovery
28626617.description: Picked up a small piece of glass in my toe. The good thing about glass compared to a splinter is that the scraping of tweezer on glass makes it easy to know when you got it.

36655003.title: Trail run at Clear Creek Metro Park
36655003.description: Nice crisp Christmas morning trail run. Didn't see any other humans except for the park ranger. Lots of hills!

35978559.title: Track - 6 x 1000m
35978559.description: Track workout - 6 x 1000m with 200m rest. Legs started tired, sore, and even a bit crampy (outside calves, behind the knee, up into the outer quad) but I made it through. Splits: 3:47, 3:41, 3:39, 3:35, 3:40, 3:37. Coolish but very humid this morning.

11255845.title: Swamp stadium roundtrip
11255845.description: New pair of black Altra Instincts. Awesome!

2648716.title: easy morning barefoot run
2648716.description: The lady across the street shouted "Dan!  You run barefoot?".  I said "Sometimes!".  After an initial reaction that I read to be similar to "yikes", she shouted "Good for you!".

23359223.title: Harris Branch area
23359223.description: A few stiff and sore spots.

33702808.title: Track workout 14 x 400m
33702808.description: On the track with Dan Clark's workout group. 14 x 400m track workout with mostly 200m rest in between each rep. (or about 1:20 rest). Kicked ass today and able to hang with the fast guys... thru 12 reps at least. On the last 2 my legs were gone and I was completely gassed. Looking through my training logs, I have never done more than ten reps previously, and the paces today were consistently faster, so good quality workout. Splits: 77, 76, 73, 77, 77, 75, 77, 76, 77, 76, 75, 75, 81, 81

34727487.description: Preview of San Felasco Gate2Gate ultra course by Patrick G. on the way out. Included Conquistador on the way back.
34727487.title: San Felasco Trails

28292311.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

15866057.title: greenways and Brywood hills
15866057.description: Hot. Some of the footbridges had been washed away so I had to backtrack and find a log to cross the creek.

34619104.title: Tempo
34619104.description: Tempo run on Glen Springs Road and 16th Ave. Got mentally distracted in the middle. Overall felt harder than expected, couldn't keep my breathing under control.

35122189.title: Track 5 x 1000m with add-on 400m
35122189.description: Track workout 5 x 1000m with add-on 400m. (rest 200m between 1000m, 600m before final 400m). Legs were not fresh and hammies screaming by the end, but a good workout on a cold morning. Splits: 3:37, 3:30, 3:33, 3:26, 3:25. 1:07 for final 400m.

33876937.description: I need to remember that I won't feel peppy the day after a hard track workout.
33876937.title: Hawthorne Trail

3880734.title: Brywood hills
3880734.description: Tried to run easy. Felt difficult. Family has been disrupting my sleep lately. Nike Frees were ok for a hill workout.  Annoyed with my Achilles tendon (or is it annoyed with me?).

3677315.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
3677315.description: Jogging with the kids.  I like my new trail shoes.  It will be good to give them a real test on some real trails one of these days. I want to let my feet heal up well first.

32822991.title: San Felasco trails - Conquistador
32822991.description: Conquistador at San Felasco. Got a late start so it was pretty warm by the end. There was a nice breeze most of the time, though.

18095314.title: night easy run
18095314.description: Yay, a run!  Still working out the kinks from whatever the heck happened to me earlier in the week. Felt like I had to do something tonight after pizza, beer, and giant fudge brownie. Now for sleep since I have a track workout in the morning.

11636265.description: The more I run in my Altra Adams the more I like them.
11636265.title: another Altra Adam run

3070674.title: warm up and cool down for race

10773277.title: I'm keeping the Inov-8 Bare-X 150
10773277.description: First run in my new Inov-8 Bare-X 150 shoes. Zero-drop goodness. Firm cushion. Seems to have just enough room in the toe box. I'll be keeping them.

36275637.title: hill sprints and fitness pit
36275637.description: hill sprints x 7 and then to fitness pit. Nice breeze.

12326310.title: good morning
12326310.description: Perfect weather for running!  Didn't feel like I was working hard at all. My Moc3s are still doing great.

2586417.description: I actually felt fast during parts of the run.  My calves are sore but other parts of my lower legs (top of foot, ankle) seem to be ok.  It helps to go into a minimalist run starting fresh and without existing lower leg aches, tiredness, and stiffness.  I think my Nikes are still more forgiving on bad technique and tired legs.  My cardio is finally good enough where I can hold the tempo and technique (and keep "lifting") long enough to finish one of these runs in minimalist footwear.
2586417.title: Morning run in Bikilas... my longest run in VFF and my fastest pace yet in dailymile

31629263.description: Just a slow shuffle. Lingering pains in both feet. Left Achilles tendon area and ankle. Right outside ankle and inside top of foot. Actually had these yesterday during my long run, so marking this entry with the injured icon. Just think I need to back of for a few days.  Update 1.26.2015: Seems that I have a swollen ankle on left side, maybe from a twist/sprain, not really the Achilles. Still sore to touch 10 days later.
31629263.title: VFF shuffle

17929135.description: Barefoot.  Legs feeling better today, I should be good to go for tomorrow's hard track workout.
17929135.title: The Daily

35486611.title: Campus B loop
35486611.description: Death by humidity! Took my Wave Universe 3 to work so a coworker could feel how light they are. Haven't run in them in maybe years so I decided to give them another try. They provide pretty good insulation from hot pavement so I will probably keep them at the office... but I could definitely tell they are not zero drop even with only 4mm differential.

33135614.description: Felt old and sore! Cool and misty.
33135614.title: BU XC course trail

23141617.description: Legs still tired and feet still a little sore from the 25-mile weekend adventure.
23141617.title: morning

29161128.description: Easy run and 6 x steep hill sprints.  Felt fine during, but I have lingering pain in upper hammy / glutes after this. Walking the fine line near overdoing it.
29161128.title: campus and steep hill sprints

30837143.title: afternoon campus
30837143.description: Warm. Been spoiled by all the cool morning weather.

14719294.description: Nice barefoot beach run at Anastasia Island State Park.  Legs were tired from my morning run but I had no trouble getting warmed up (it was downright hot when the wind was at my back).
14719294.title: Barefoot on the beach

27889560.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

30495424.description: Added a little effort for that last bit.
30495424.title: progression

22982143.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

35542790.description: Fizzled out big time at the end. Finished around 11am in the sun and heat.
35542790.title: Bacon Strip 11

18353959.title: Work to Morningside Nature Center
18353959.description: My body does not seem to like to run when it is expecting lunch.  Definitely warm and humid out there, I was *completely* drenched with sweat by the time I got back to work.  Ran to Cone Park and then the perimeter trail (blue blazes = 3 miles?) of Morningside Nature Center. No impassable sections due to water even though it rained this morning.  Did a poor job of keeping time while stopped at Cone Park.

34037775.description: Beautiful Florida fall day. Ran from campus to the Alachua Lake Overlook. I saw lots of wildlife despite being mid-day... wild turkeys, a raccoon, and three snakes!
34037775.title: campus to Hawthorne Trail Alachua Lake Overlook

33579469.title: progression
33579469.description: 9 minute pace for the first 5 miles, averaged about 7:30 pace for the last 3.

35599226.description: Tropical Storm Colin on the way! Snuck a run in (mostly) between rain bands.
35599226.title: campus

28496883.description: Run across campus with a former coworker. Did a few stadiums and strides on the track but otherwise easy jogging. Then to Burrito Bros. for lunch!
28496883.title: campus

12847348.description: Had to walk a few times when the foot/ankle thing started hurting.
12847348.title: Brywood hills

29974068.description: Running with Dan Clark rarely makes for an easy day.
29974068.title: San Felasco trails

18899245.description: Still recovering from the 25-miler and it has been a rough work and family week. Thinking of the folks who are running the NYC Marathon. Splits: 1:30, 1:29, 1:18
18899245.title: 3 x 400m

10486695.description: Felt pretty good, ran in my Moc3s at a pretty good pace. I slowed in the middle but then realized I was LATE and had to speed home to take the kids to school.  Hip tensors still feeling weak from the trail race.
10486695.title: early morning Moc3

25698306.description: Included a little tempo work. 1.7 miles in 13:18 is 7:49 per mile, not very fast! I don't want to try doing speed yet (post-50k), no idea how long my recovery ought to be. Update: this was the last run prior to the foot pain in my right big toe / met area. No pain during this run but started next day I think.
25698306.title: Chilly!

29412862.title: Melon Run 2014 race
29412862.description: Melon Run 2014, 3 mile race. Hot and Humid. Didn't go out too hard and fast. Won my age group and brought home a watermelon. First mile 6:09. Finish time of 17:46 (5:43 avg. per mile) was just a few seconds slower than last year.

34573674.description: Ran my San Felasco trails gate-to-gate hilly route which now includes part of Conquistador for 18 miles total. Legs are spent. Cold and rainy but a nice day on the trails. Glad to have Jason S. for company.
34573674.title: cold and rainy San Felasco hills

17288827.title: morning
17288827.description: Still very sore in the quads and calves but otherwise doing ok. Breaking in new shoes... Inov-8 Bare-X Lite 150. This is my second pair of 150s only this time I found them in ORANGE. I really like them as a road racing shoe and they have good grip on mondo track surface.

32151679.title: The Daily
32151679.description: Been fighting a terrible head cold and headaches for 2 days. It is barefoot weather!

15162606.title: warm down
15162606.description: Basically fizzled during my run long run, this was when I decided to stop and just jog it easy the rest of the way home.

28436602.title: San Felasco trails tempo run
28436602.description: Felt incredibly strong during my trail tempo run today. I was not sure how things would go because I had a lot of strange pains in my legs (due to the steep hill sprinting earlier in the week). Warmed up for almost 50 minutes and things felt good during the tempo run itself. Time between signs Hammock Cutoff to Sand Hill Cutoff 10:17. 19:45 total which is 7 seconds faster than last week at what felt like less effort.

11628810.title: very slow
11628810.description: Not feeling great the past few days.  Just wanted to get out a little to get the blood flowing.

34588065.title: a Coach Will track workout
34588065.description: Coach Dan wasn't at the track this morning so Luke got us a Coach Will workout. 1600m, 100m rest, 300m hard straight into a 1600m, 200m rest, 200m hard straight into another 1600m, 100m hard.  The goal was to run each 1600m faster than the previous and I nailed that part. mile splits: 6:28, 6:05, 5:54

14205503.title: nice morning
14205503.description: 40 Mile Week!  Broke out the Bare-X 150s for the first time in a while, they felt good. Stadium was still gated everywhere so I couldn't do stairs today, and of course the UF track is closed on weekends.  Incorporated some long incline intervals on the way home along NW 23rd St (by the arboretum) and NW 25th Terrace.

2978380.description: That place was BUSY today.  Ran half of Cathy B.'s workout.  Over 10 miles, that's my new longest run!
2978380.title: San Felasco

24684069.description: Fit2Run 10k Cross Country Challenge race. Rainy, sloppy, muddy, fun, AWESOME!  I earned 2nd overall and even got a 10k age group PR out of it with 38:16.  My NB Minimus Trail MT00 shoes did great, no trouble in the slippery sections, great traction, they drained well and didn't absorb water. Mile Splits: 6:24, 6:33, 6:22, 6:22, 6:32, 6:02 (last 1.2 miles, maybe the course was a little short?).  Thanks Dan C. for the post-race beer!
24684069.title: Fit2Run 10k Cross Country Challenge race

9069470.description: Ran from our rental house in Blowing Rock on Appalachian Ski Mountain down to highway 321 and back.  There were some pretty steep sections.
9069470.title: Blue Ridge mountain roads

2530085.description: Gave my RunAmocs another try. That's probably the last time I run in them. A combination of the moccasin design that has too little internal height and probably wearing a size too small puts too much pressure on my big toenail.
2530085.title: RunAmoc trial 2

27603489.title: Trails with hills at San Felasco
27603489.description: Figuring out a good hill route. Estimated distance. Ran parts of this at hard effort.  Time between signs Hammock Cutoff to Sand Hill Cutoff 10:20.  Starting to feel ready for racing.

2148453.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
2148453.description: Ran in my Nike Free Run+ because my calves and foot were not feeling happy.  After all the running barefoot and in minimal shoes, I think my feet are more sensitive and I could feel "through" the insole to all of the bumps and ridges in the support structure... and one shoe felt different than the other.  I felt a hard ridge under the ball of the right foot.  It was very distracting and my foot eventually started hurting.

16529127.title: morning easy run
16529127.description: Taking it easy trying to get over a sinus thing and get my Achilles tendon issue completely resolved.

34228694.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
34228694.description: Nice evening. Cooler weather is here!

23409843.description: Austin has a great trail system! Not exactly sure how far along I went on the Barton Springs Greenway. The rocky parts were not very much fun in my Vapor Gloves so I turned around after a while and was glad to get back onto the softer paths.
23409843.title: Austin Hilton to Barton Springs Greenway

3616338.title: UF campus with Dwight and Matt
3616338.description: First run since Sunday.  Still some sinus mayhem but feeling much better overall.  Rest is good.  Most of the body felt fresh.  Dwight made us push up the hills on Gale Lemerand Drive.  Left Achilles still touchy.  Right calf feels a little strained.

3363698.description: Yay for LSD (Long Slow Distance). Got very hot at the end (noon).  I think this is my longest run in VFF.  No arch pains or any of the other issues that I used to get from VFF.  I guess my form is much improved.
3363698.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

31714305.title: recovery
31714305.description: Windy! Overall legs tired, calves very sore, and left Achilles a bit tender this morning.

8035227.title: run in the rain
8035227.description: Bend the knees, bend the knees.  Run lightly.  The foot should kiss the ground like an airplane coming in for a landing.  Felt pretty good in my VFF although I had some rubbing around the toe pockets.  My body finally revolted against all that rest by giving me horrible heartburn / acid reflux last night. Prior to this, I hadn't had any noticeable heartburn over the whole last year since I started running.  I had to get out and move tonight to keep the stomach acid at bay.

29261659.title: warm up and down
29261659.description: Warming up with friend Matt who is doing couch to 5k.

10175526.description: Perfect running weather. Intense.  Achilles tendons still nagging me on these morning runs.  Altra Instincts yeah baby.
10175526.title: no sidewalks

22034808.title: LGAA 5k
22034808.description: Very warm. Missed my chance to beat Dan Monteau, I just couldn't get myself to go faster and push into that next level of pain. 4th overall with a time of 18:35.

36159352.description: Going easy and barefoot to help get over my injury (piriformis). Cooler weather is nice, too.
36159352.title: barefoot morning

17872003.title: warmup / cooldown
17872003.description: Pretty warm and humid, not much warmup needed.

10410751.title: barefoot run with work buddies
10410751.description: One guy runs in VFF, one runs barefoot.  I ran barefoot.  Exactly what I needed.

30650140.title: Dog Days 5k race
30650140.description: Nice morning for the Dog Days 5k race. Finished 18:20 for the Masters win and 2nd overall on a course with some tough hills.  Good day!

32029025.title: track workout short intervals
32029025.description: Gentle re-introduction to fast track intervals. 2 x 400m (1:20,1:19), 4 x 200m (33s, 32s, 33s, 32s).

33894888.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

24523909.description: Included 1 mile of stride the straights, jog the curves.
24523909.title: warm up and down

3510427.title: Brywood to 13th St
3510427.description: Tissues are still recovering from the long weekend run.

15205243.description: After some warmup, tagged along with other folks on a progression run, 3 loops x 5k each. The last 5k was 20:18 (6:30 pace). It seems to be a sparse time of year for 5k races around here, this was exactly what I needed. Great group of people out there tonight!
15205243.title: group run at Austin Cary Memorial Forest

14306019.description: Nice evening race on the Ironwood golf course, a mix of grass and paved cart path. The smoke from nearby fires seemed to have cleared before the race which was good.  However, it was still hot.  Had a decent race but fizzled a bit on mile 3, wasn't really mentally prepared for the pain and suffering.  Won my age group and 7th overall.  I was invited to run in the team challenge, our team got 2nd place which means a donation to Tyler's Hope (a foundation for research into treating Dystonia).  Felt good to contribute to the team effort.
14306019.title: LGAA 5k

24853657.title: San Felasco trails
24853657.description: Started early and got in some good miles. Happy to find some TERRAIN. Ran from the south side to the north side and stopped before getting lost. Stuck mostly to the horse trails. There are actually some really nice, rugged single track horse trails on the north side.

33935395.description: In the noonday heat! 2 x 4.25 mile tempo with 4 minute rest in between. Had some trouble keeping focus. Pretty consistent pace for each segment (same route each): 29:32, 29:30
33935395.title: Tempo Run 2 x 4.25 Mi

6838024.title: barefoot
6838024.description: Went easy except for when I ramped up to top speed for a stretch, feeling out whether I could do a serious race barefoot.  Tore my feet up a little.  Not ready for fast barefoot yet.

11469189.description: Stayed close to home, ran for the first time with phone and pager.  I'm in the middle of my first week of being on-call at my new job (I'm on a team of system administrators).  Had a rough weekend, very little sleep.  Re-used an old mp3 player arm band for the pager, but splurged on an android-friendly arm band for the phone. Wore my VFF for the first time in a while since it was wet and yucky out.
11469189.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

21288484.title: First night run in a while
21288484.description: Big dinner. Cold night. Nice run.

15211069.title: recovery run
15211069.description: A little sore from yesterday's effort but a nice morning run.

21858348.title: Waldo Road
21858348.description: Feeling a little flat after a few crazy weeks with travel and irregular sleep / disrupted running schedule. Included a 3 mile out-and-back tempo run, Splits: 10:26 (6:57 per mile), 9:28 (6:18 per mile).  Warm enough today to get that hot dry burning mouth and throat feeling.

19390204.title: Yasso 800s on the track
19390204.description: Yasso 800s. This time I was able to finish all 10 reps and thus complete the workout. Still liking my Altra Samsons for track workouts. Kept the recovery lap at around 2 minutes, not just a jog.  Splits: 3:10, 3:11, 3:07, 3:01, 3:03, 3:01, 2:53, 3:00, 3:05, 2:55.  Average time for 10 reps was 3:02, so if you believe Yassos are predictive of marathon time I might have a shot at going under 3 hours or at least getting a BQ (need 3 hrs 10 min). Today I also learned that Hammer Gel packets are hard to open with cold fingers. Now... for recovery. Tom Walker Half Marathon is only 2 days away.

4909590.description: I thought I would give my Nike Free Run+ another try. Still burning off high-energy beer soups.  Didn't have any knee issues (which is why I quit running in my Frees). My ankles were happy to have some cushion I think, although it was hard to find my midfoot with the raised heel. I aggravated my Achilles a little bit (I was actually hoping the heel would help).  Also ended up with blisters on my big toes, even with socks, confirming that the toe box in the Frees is too narrow.  Will have a clean conscience when I buy new shoes next month. :)
4909590.title: Now that I have learned how to run...

35587204.description: In the heat. 3 x one-third mile hill repeats, just doing some brisk work to stay sharp but didn't push too hard. My way up upper hamstrings and glutes were still sore from previous hard workout.  Splits: 2:08, 2:00, 1:55.
35587204.title: one-third mile hill repeats

11560999.title: Barefoot Treadmill
11560999.description: It was a nice treadmill for running barefoot, I didn't get hot feet like I have heard happens sometimes.  Seems like the treadmill may have been lying about the distance, although I did have the incline cranked up the whole time.  Did some fartleks by cranking the speed up a few times.

35255883.description: Track workout - Ladder 4-3-2-1 aka 1600m, 1200m, 800m, 400m with 400m recoveries at moderate pace, not a jog. Paced Richard through this one. Splits (Recoveries): 6:31 (1:58), 5:05 (2:08), 3:21 (2:08), 1:32
35255883.title: Track workout - Ladder 4-3-2-1

26359996.title: The Daily
26359996.description: See that happy face?  Felt good. Had another round of self deep tissue massage in my foot last night, again seems to help.

13225301.description: Nice average pace considering I know the first few miles were around 10 minute pace.  Got into a groove after 45 minutes and I was moving well, but then the wheels feel off at the 1 hour mark.  A bit later I realized I was late getting home so I had to haul it in quickly.  No foot pain today!
13225301.title: moc3 woot

32903971.title: Hill sprints
32903971.description: warm up and 8 x campus hill sprints

28944919.description: Got in a few more miles barefoot.
28944919.title: barefoot

18524721.title: Moc3 tempo
18524721.description: Such a nice cool crisp morning (finally!) with temps in the low 60s. Ran the last two miles in 13:30 (6:45 per mile). Quads were still feeling tired from last week, it was good to skip the track workout today. I have been neglecting to do eccentric heel lifts for my Achilles tendons. I need to get that back into my routine.

10036573.title: depletion run
10036573.description: No breakfast, no fuel, only water to drink. I recently acquired a slightly-used pair of Altra Instincts which were great for this run.

26579026.title: out and back
26579026.description: Yay, something resembling a decent pace.

30020122.title: Track workout
30020122.description: Muscles a little sore but I mostly hit my targets on the track. 5 x 400m, 3 x 800m with the 400s at 5 minute per mile pace and the 800s under 6 minute pace. Had a hard time getting mentally back into it for the 800s. Splits: 400m 1:13, 1:15, 1:15, 1:15, 1:15, water break, 800m 3:13, 2:59, 2:58 (recoveries were all under 2 minutes, 200m jog).

14752457.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
14752457.description: Slow and easy out, picked it up on the way back. It's no fun fighting bodily functions during a run.

17872198.title: Monthly group run at Austin Cary Memorial Forest
17872198.description: Austin Cary Memorial Forest group run. Humid! Ran 3 x 5k. Splits: 26:11, 22:06, 22:00. This hard effort caps off a 50 mile week. Woot!  As always, a nice group of people were out for this run through the forest. My Altra Instinct 1.5 shoes really liked the packed limerock road surface.

31440148.description: Still recovering from multi-day sinus mayhem and migraines. Looked at the calendar though... time to lay down the marathon training plan!
31440148.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

20752025.description: What did I do while I was sick? Watched a lot of running videos, read some running book, and tried to determine what was up with my gait. Think I figured it out (crossover gait due to pelvis "dipping"), started doing some drills, I feel like I have improvement already. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LG-xLi2m5Rc
20752025.title: The Daily

23558050.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

17675435.title: Long run with zig zag thru campus
17675435.description: Fasted LSD morning run, had nothing but water before the run, didn't carry, and had only two water stops. Not sure if my body missed the food or the caffeine more. I'm surprised by my calculated pace, based on how I felt I thought I'd be much slower. It was foggy through most of the run and it felt like a lukewarm sauna. Altra Instincts are still my go-to shoe for the long run. Lots of Gator tailgaters setting up for the first football game of the season.

15519592.title: Brywood hills
15519592.description: Hill loop again, this time in Altra Sampsons. Wanted to compare to the Merrell Trail Gloves. I think I like the Sampsons better for roads (not surprising).

30930103.title: campus and Biven's Arm Conservation Area
30930103.description: Had to walk carefully through some of the trail sections. Saw some gators!

5493130.description: Seemed to have extra energy tonight (it's hard not to eat a lot on weekends) so I went for a second run of the day.  Felt good.  Beautiful, beautiful weather.  About halfway through the run I remembered the beer that I drank earlier.  Finally found my stride in my MWU3 shoes.  Great running week, no injuries!

11518463.title: 8th Ave short flat
11518463.description: Just wanted to get some more miles in... this time in my Instincts.

8875026.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
8875026.description: A nice morning for a barefoot run.

7386829.description: New shoes are the RunAmoc DASH Smooth by Soft Star Shoes.  Bought them to be my new daily work shoes but decided to give them a try running.  Great great improvements over the previous RunAmoc LITE.  Mine have the trail sole which makes them a bit heavy (probably heavier than my Altra Instincts).  A fun shoe.  Would make a great XC option for some people.
7386829.title: jog to the track in new RunAmoc DASH

8120393.title: barefoot run
8120393.description: Barefoot running off part of the extra slice of stuffed crust pizza I ate.

35920202.title: greenways
35920202.description: First run with new Salomon S-Lab Sense Ultra Set hydration vest. Usually use handhelds so this is new experience for me.

12163543.description: I had to run barefoot on such a nice day!
12163543.title: Barefoot!

35154460.title: San Felasco trails
35154460.description: Nice run with Hunter. Super humid!

9069633.title: Blue Ridge Mountains Tanawha Trail
9069633.description: Awesome difficult trail running in the Blue Ridge Mountains.  Got on the Tanawha Trail at the Cold Prong parking area and ran uphill to the boardwalk at Rough Ridge.  The trails were rooty and rocky and beautiful.  Didn't see another human except for the guy who convinced me (thank you!) to continue on up the trail to Rough Ridge.  The views of Grandfather Mountain and the surrounding area were spectacular.  Soft Star RunAmoc DASH with trail sole were awesome for this run.  The trail sole had plenty of protection from the roots and traction was great on the rounded boulders of the Appalachians.  According to my watch I was actually 10 minutes slower on the way down than the way up.  I did not run with GPS but according to this site I believe the elevation of my run ranged from 3600 feet - 4600 feet.  http://b-fick.com/gps/2008/tanawha-trail

3522230.title: UF campus
3522230.description: Feel drained.  I have some kind of sinus thing going on.  Achilles is still bothering me.

20548022.description: There is some *very* twisty single track near my house that makes a half mile loop. Seems like a good place to run trail intervals. Lots of different muscles activating. My legs feel way better after than they did before the workout. 2 x half mile splits: 4:10, 3:57
20548022.title: half-mile trail repeats

7301499.title: that... felt... weird
7301499.description: Started off feeling easy but then got light-headed.  Stopped to walk a few times.  Seemed disconnected from my body's signals.  I'm sure the heat played a role but overall just felt weird.

33813152.title: track workout
33813152.description:
Track workout. Fell. Off. Hard. about halfway through. 1600m (5:28), 1200m (4:08), 800m (2:38), 800m (3:00), 400m (1:28), 400m (1:25)
edit: ended up getting terrible headache and felt pretty yucky all day... must be fighting a bug.

35512945.description: Legs tired but it is a nice sunny day, not too hot, with a breeze.
35512945.title: fitness pit and 10 x steep hill sprints

5188136.description:
Don't like running in my Nike Frees anymore, but wanted the cushion for my chappy feet.  I long for a pair of Altra Running Instincts:
http://altrarunning.com/mens/instinct/
5188136.title: University Ave 6mi loop

15284867.title: 9 miler
15284867.description: Now that I am on a lower-carb diet and I'm eating many more whole foods, I can really tell when I fall off the wagon. I ate 3 doughnuts yesterday (the breakroom at work is *killing* me). Ended up feeling spaced out, had low energy, low motivation, maybe even a bit depressed. I have to wonder whether a few years ago I always felt so crummy or if now I get a much harder swing than I used to.  Hopefully this morning's run burned out the crud.

4195427.title: San Felasco Yellow loop
4195427.description: Switched to MWU3... night and day compared to the Adidas Kanadias.  This loop felt much better.  Total for the day was 17.8 miles.

5214889.title: The Armadillo Run at San Felasco
5214889.description: I saw five armadillos today, my all-time single-day high.  Stopped to look at a few of them so lost a little time there. Ran the outer loop (blue+yellow) with Sandhill Cutoff. That trail is nice, it is the first time I tried it... mostly grass and pine needles instead of the loose sand.  Shortens the route by .5 miles.  Still getting a little twitch in my right glute (from two weeks ago when I bumped up my mileage too much) and the blistery foot has a few places where the skin is dry/cracked.  It was nice to be on trails again, it feels like it has been a long time.

11282653.title: 39th Ave Loop
11282653.description: Brisk morning with cool, clear skies. Lots of stars.  Quads still sore from Wednesday's stadium stairs but overall a nice run in my Moc3s.

11146675.description: Course was great, well-marked with lots of grass like a Cross Country course.  The excitement got to me and I went out too fast, I was way ahead of my breathing and hurting for most of the race.  Wore my Soft Star RunAmoc Smooth moccasins.  They were awesome on the grassy and trail sections, did fine on the road sections.  One thing I didn't like about the course is that we caught up to the slow walkers with their strollers and kids, so I had to weave and dodge in the last mile to avoid plowing through some people or running over the little ones who stopped right in front of me to pick something up off the trail.  Lots of good runners there today, luckily overall awards went 3-deep so I managed to win my age group. Official time 40:27. Mile splits:  6:08, 6:27, 6:43, 6:47, 6:32, 6:36.
11146675.title: Gainesville Turkey Trot 10k

24254190.title: Track workout 14 x 500m
24254190.description: Track workout 14 x 500m with 100m recovery (40 - 50 seconds).  Average splits were around 1:50 (5:54 mile pace) which is a little slower than I wanted.  I have been feeling some systemic tiredness but I was still able to put in a good hard effort, so overall happy with the workout. Next week no track workout.

20937551.title: Five Points of Life 5k
20937551.description: Considering how my running felt this week coming off being sick, my calves were still a little sore from Thursday's track workout, and the fact that I tweaked my knee yesterday walking up some stairs, I'm very much ok with this run. I felt good. Weather was perfect. 4th overall and won my age group. Didn't get any of my splits.

16484917.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

18706920.description: Easy recovery run. Nice cool morning for a run in my Soft Star mocs.
18706920.title: Santa Fe water stop out-and-back

21043013.description: Plus a few miles of warmup around the track.
21043013.title: short round trip UF track

3358253.description: Long runs must have magical healing powers... the almost 10 miles I ran this morning seem to have cleared out all the kinks.  Or maybe it was the bean and corn burritos I made for lunch gave me super powers.  This evening I went for a short barefoot walk/run with my daughter and felt good, so then I went for a run by myself.  Everything felt great, had to take advantage and fly fly fly.
3358253.title: awesome barefoot run

15071336.description: Today was the session running in shoes, my Altra Instincts. I now have a disc full of high speed video and a bunch of data to look over. Interestingly, it looks like me running barefoot requires more energy than in cushioned shoes. Temper that with some form issues that seem more pronounced in those same shoes.
15071336.title: mostly treadmill - running study day 2

8167037.title: Melon Run 3 mile race - Barefoot
8167037.description: My first barefoot race on mostly paved surface. This course has about a half mile on greenway boardwalk / dirt trail, the rest was sidewalk and street.  Definitely went out a little too fast but held on for top-3 in my age group which earned me a watermelon!  My main goal was to race but keep my barefoot form and avoid blisters.  My feet are in good shape with just a few hot spots so I feel like I met my goal.

35928366.description: humid! Got some good experience with my Salomon S-Lab Sense Ultra Set hydration vest.
35928366.title: San Felasco trails

28699927.title: Track fizzle
28699927.description: Warm and humid. Fizzled again. Mentally could not push myself today. Planned to ladder 1600, 1200, 800, 400. Finished 1600m and 800m. Splits (recovery): 5:28 (4:53), 2:59.  Warm up included 800m of stride straights on the track. No hill sprints today.

28010176.title: Trail of Payne 10k race
28010176.description: Trail of Payne 10k race. Warm and soggy (humid). Different course than last year due to trails underwater. There was still plenty of mud and water to run through. Not the performance I was hoping for. Finish time 40:55. Splits: 6:15, 6:20, 6:30, 6:53, 7:02,  6:44, 1:10

35641287.description: Campus and 6 x steep hill sprints. Very warm!
35641287.title: campus and 6 x steep hill sprints

20659729.description: Nose running like a faucet since last night.
20659729.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway

5608268.description: First time I ran without a shirt in a LONG time.  Felt hot today in this Florida sunshine.  Probably should have limited myself to 2 or 3 miles barefoot since my feet were complaining a bit at the end.
5608268.title: Barefoot and shirtless

16950930.description: Ran from home to the stadium, did the group run around Lake Alice, then ran home. A small but nice group of people were there for the group run.
16950930.title: group run on campus

32319125.title: easy
32319125.description: Some pains inside my feet. Taking it easy.

31767646.title: cold long run
31767646.description: Legs started feeling tired after 2 hours, especially at the hip flexors. Left ankle sore and tender again (just above the medial malleolus).

3813641.description: Switched to VFF.  Was going to run another outer loop but quickly realized just how bad the VFF Bikila are on sandy trails.  I quickly hopped over and decided to do Hammock Cutoff.  After a time developed some pain in my right arch.
3813641.title: San Felasco - Hammock Cutoff loop

35419116.description: Boom! Fastest quarter mile I have run in years. 61 seconds makes me think I have a chance of going under a minute for 400m. This was a time trial fun race with my friend Richard G.
35419116.title: 400m track race

35149654.title: Trail of Payne 10k
35149654.description: Ha ha great morning for the Trail of Payne 10k trail race. Rains came through during the night and left a nice muddy fun mess. Ran my race plan well, finished strong. 1st Masters. Splits: 6:23, 6:32, 6:37, 6:27, 6:16, 6:24, 1:26

35784188.description: First run in VFF EL-X LS that I bought off ebay. Big toe felt a little snug but hopefully that will stretch with use.
35784188.title: neighborhoods

36124044.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
36124044.description: Spent most of the time clearing trails on the greenway after Hurricane Hermine. Packed my little folding hand saw in my Salomon vest, worked great for transport. Super humid!

24887328.title: Santa Fe water stop out-and-back

23087435.description: A long day of trail running at San Felasco in the heat wearing my Merrell Vapor Gloves. I started the morning by exploring the hiking trails on the south side of Millhopper Road. Then I followed blue blaze trail to a service road, crossed the gate into the wilderness area, and ended up on horse trails on the north side of the park. Lots of mountain bikes out today. I wandered on curvy singletrack to the north parking area to refill my water bottles and cool down. I was hot and tired by this point (3 hours in and approaching noon), so I wanted to avoid the singletrack on the way back. I needed to get to the bridges near the Soggy Bottom / CreekSide loops to hop back on the horse trails and find that gate. Never did find my way. Next time I will take a map. After getting lost, using up all my food and gels, and almost running out of water, I decided to cross the wilderness swamp that I had used in years past (follow the powerlines). I didn't need to wade through anything more than ankle-deep water (whew!). I did a lot walking during that last hour. I was glad to arrive back at my car with cold water and food waiting for me. Today was a nice adventure (despite the biting flies and ticks), and I saw a couple of hawks, a big wise old owl, some deer (including a cute little fawn), and a large herd of feral pigs. Love the Vapor Gloves.
23087435.title: All over San Felasco

Glad to have running buddies out there early in the morning (thanks Stephanie, Meredith, and John D.).  The track was really really really crowded.  Felt good enough after to finish with some surges on the long gentle uphills on my run home.
17633430.title: track workout 10 x 400m

30576982.description: WoBtoberfest 5k was a great little race. I placed 2nd overall and earned the 1st place Masters award. Delicious free beer after! Finish time 18:18.
30576982.title: WoBtoberfest 5k race

3207070.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

11255893.title: Stadium Stairs
11255893.description: 6 x Stadium Stairs at the Swamp. Good enough to get some hamstring cramps on the run home.

25595539.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

17219132.title: near the stadium
17219132.description: Warming up before hitting the stairs.

7044724.description: Seven uphill repeats with recovery in-between.  Splits:  2:08 / 2:03 / 2:01 / 2:00 / 2:01 / 1:56 / 1:55.  Recoveries ranged from 2:43 - 3:49.
7044724.title: one-third mile hill repeats

4167004.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
4167004.description: Started *really* slowly... last night involved beerific carbo loading. Included 4 fartleks.

33968116.description: Easy pace and then some progressive increase in the middle up towards full speed. Great temperature.
33968116.title: nice nice cool morning

28112999.title: Flatwoods 5k race
28112999.description: Flatwoods 5k race at Austin Cary Forest.  Ran 18:11 this year compared to 18:27 last year.  Had a good pace through the first 2 miles (thanks Hutson and Michael!). Mile Splits: 5:45, 5:53, 6:02.  Based on video and photographic evidence from my last few races, I have let my form slip into bad habits. This was only day 2 of form corrections. I also think I know what I need to do in training (more time in the pain zone) so looking forward to continued improvement.

8289493.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

5969880.title: easy barefoot before work
5969880.description: Seems like I had a good, therapeutic morning in prep for tomorrow 10k Trail of Payne.  Easy barefoot run with icing after.  My Achilles area and ankles are feeling good.

5925230.description: Started out great running at cruise speed. Ended poorly.  Hamstrings were still sore from the weekend.  Developed twinges around my knees and achilles.  The raised heel on the NB Minimus is the most likely cause, it definitely affects my stride.  Finally gave up and barefooted it home.
5925230.title: nice weather

31694457.description: Track workout 8 x 1000m after 12.5 miles of "warmup". Over 20 miles total on the day. Splits: 3:50, 3:46, 3:50, 3:46, 3:45, 3:43, 3:42, 3:37 (pace range 6:10 - 5:49 per mile).
31694457.title: Track workout 8 x 1k

2363194.title: barefoot
2363194.description: Played "follow the leader" with my 3-year old.  We ended up barefoot running through the woods.  It was fun!

29364417.description: Took advantage of the forest trails after my group finished its annual retreat.
29364417.title: Austin Cary Forest

20917876.title: morning shakedown
20917876.description: 400 miles on my Soft Star Moc3 shoes!

24524049.title: Time trial 1600m and 400m
24524049.description: I'm well into my taper so I ran some fast time trials instead of a workout. Legs felt pretty good.  Solo 1600m in 5:16, 400m in 63s. I was hoping to go under 5 min. for the 1600m which I didn't hit but still an improvement. Happy with the 400m, getting closer to going under a minute.  1600m splits: 1:13, 1:21, 1:23, 1:19

3981435.description: Ran the first 7 miles with Matt C.  He was targeting a 2 hour finish time (and he made it!  We ran mostly between 9:00 - 9:30 pace for the first 7). I left him (as we agreed) and then I started to push it. I was able to pick off runners the whole way back. Developed a knot in my right quad muscle.  Started pumping the gatorade at every aid station, the quad didn't end up being an issue.  Felt like I finished fairly strong.  The new shoes (MWU3) did fine.
3981435.title: Tom Walker Memorial Half Marathon

3059152.description: Woke up early feeling crummy, headache, a little hungover, couldn't get back to sleep.  Slipped out of the house quietly with my feet completely free.  My first barefoot run in the dark.  Rubbed off a little skin which unfortunately means I probably won't race barefoot tomorrow.  I have been pounding out the miles in my Nike Frees.  I guess "pounding" is the keyword here... I started having knee pain earlier in the week even though I have been maintaining a forefoot / mid-foot strike.  Still had the pain this morning until after the first mile, but running barefoot forced me to run lighter and now the joint pain is gone.  I'm a believer.
3059152.title: barefoot 4 miles

34447723.title: Track workout 6 x 1000m
34447723.description: Track workout 6 x 1000m on a wet sloppy day. Why do we do six reps? Because everyone else does five. Mostly 200m (under 1:30) recoveries. Splits: 3:27, 3:42, 3:47, 3:46, 3:38, 3:42  Not bad after my recent speed hiatus.

13080868.description: Legs sore from increased volume.  The gimpy foot was feeling a little bit... gimpy.  Took it easy had a nice run.
13080868.title: morning

13341395.description: Repeat of yesterday's greenway trail route in Altra Instincts.  Wanted a baseline before another test run in NB Minimus Zero.
13341395.title: Greenways

13007329.title: spectating Five Points of Life
13007329.description: Run/walk/jog/wait while spectating the race.  Saw some great pacers and racers out there.  Foot feeling gimpy today and ribs still sore.  Did some plyo activities while waiting for the first runners to come through campus.

7145921.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
7145921.description: Some morning stiffness, including the knees.

35118330.title: steep hill sprints
35118330.description: we stopped and did some tire flips, dips, and pull-ups

14952082.title: mostly treadmill - running study
14952082.description: First session, barefoot, mostly on the treadmill.  http://www.ortho.ufl.edu/research/studies/barefoot-running

3941160.title: Energizer Bunny run
3941160.description: So nice to be able to run and run and run until exhausted rather than having to quit when something starts to hurt. Had a nice cool rain the whole way. New Favorite Shoes: Mizuno Wave Universe 3.

23003804.description: Things are finally getting back to normal. Very warm and humid out there!
23003804.title: greenways

3144620.title: On UF campus
3144620.description: Calves were still sore today.  It was hot.  Felt tired and slow.

28736048.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

9747168.title: greenway and singletrack
9747168.description: Last night had a little twinge around my knee so this morning I decided to go barefoot nice and slow.  A nice relaxing run on greenways and singletrack side trails.  No kinks after.

10273794.title: gentle walk and run
10273794.description: Just getting some movement in.  Been feeling worn down this week.  Gentle run with some walking here and there.

4967606.description: I thought that since my feet were warmed up I'd be able to go sockless with the sandals.  My toes got cold rather quickly and the thin sandals did not insulate from the cold ground.  I hate cold toes.  Traction was not as good as the RunAmocs on wet boardwalk.  The good news is that again my forefoot to midfoot conversion seems to make these more comfortable to wear (not so much friction in between the toes).
4967606.title: Gave the huarache sandals another try

35433161.description: Had some odd pains in my right foot at first. Legs sore from yesterday's workout.
35433161.title: warmup and down

33482348.description: 2nd run of the day. Florida Track Club social included free beers to members. Good evening!
33482348.title: First Magnitude FTC run

6382627.title: First run in Altra Instincts
6382627.description: Initial feeling is that I'll be keeping the Instincts.  They are not "minimalist" since they are very cushioned but they do support "natural" running motion.  No raised heel = no knee pain!  There is a loss of proprioception so I had to remind myself to "run light".  I am curious to see how they do on a long run.  I woke up REALLY stiff in my lower legs this morning.  Also have not been feeling great, eating junk (Easter candy has started to appear), and not enough FRUIT and VEGGIES!

36375899.title: longer round trip to track
36375899.description: Some light track work to stretch out the legs, 2 x 400m and 4 x 200m. Felt better after.

17998035.title: 8th Ave short flat
17998035.description: Barefoot and slow. Still recovering from the last few weeks of hard effort.

36371512.title: Steep hill sprints x 4
36371512.description: Nice and easy then steep hill sprints x 4

6422558.title: 3 hours in Altra Instincts
6422558.description: I have found my new Long Day shoe - the Altra Instinct.  Shoes did great on sidewalk, road, and greenway / gentle nature trails.  Just guessing at the distance and pace.  I was trying to hit 3 hours of forward motion and I made it.  I have determined that it helps tremendously to injest calories on runs this long.

36151782.title: Race the Tortoise 5k 2015
36151782.description: Race the Tortoise 5k 2015.  "Did you get a cramp?" said the 11-year old who beat me.

13061976.title: lunchtime run
13061976.description: A little warm.  No foot pain.  No sore ribs.  :)

6961965.description: That's what I'm talking about. Cardio is in good shape. Form must have broken down towards the end, started feeling some twinges in both Achilles.
6961965.title: nice night

33325813.title: San Felasco trails
33325813.description: Figure 8 of blue then yellow loop.

28239705.description: Mostly on the greenway trails. Temps in mid 80s. Wore long sleeves, pants, hat, gloves. Included 3 x hard effort intervals of 2:45 - 4:00 in length.
28239705.title: heat training - top of levees

29073239.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
29073239.description: Started off sore. Breaking in my newish (eBay!) Altra Samsons. Legs loosened up and I started visualizing my upcoming track races... pace drifted up to Moderate.

7694930.description: Time to get serious about developing my foot pads.
7694930.title: barefoot walk / run

30812344.description: Took my time warming up (alternate walk, jog). Felt fully loosened up after 40 minutes. Finished with 23 minutes of tempo (about 6:50 pace). After so many miles of twisty, rooty, single track trail yesterday, it actually felt good to run on some nice smooth sidewalk.
30812344.title: Tempo on tired legs

6137320.title: Long run in VFF
6137320.description: Took almost a whole week off after last weekend's race to see if my Achilles area would settle down.  The lack of activity actually seemed to have made it stiff and irritable, so it felt good to get out and run.  Hogtown Creek Greenway to Loblolly Woods, over to Green Acres Park, across the top of the levy to Clear Lake Nature Park, back up 8th Ave to Cofrin Nature Park, across 16th Ave and up through Alfred Ring Park, loop Glenn Springs Rd. to 34th St. and back home.  One bathroom break and two water stops, I didn't carry anything.  Ran to depletion.  A good LSD endurance run.

35433177.title: Track - 9 x 300m alternating pace
35433177.description: Track - 9 x 300m alternating pace between 3k and 1 mile pace. Short 100m jog recovery. 300m splits: 65, 58, 61, 56, 61, 55, 58, 53, 57

36307063.description: steep hill sprints x 9.  Some bad pain in piriformis area, possibly a new area that I at least was able to pinpoint but will need to research.
36307063.title: steep hill sprints x 9

20810292.title: no sidewalks
20810292.description: Really feeling the newly activated muscles from the new gait pattern (keeping the hip from dipping in during the swing phase). Nice cool morning. Out and back splits: 39:09, 40:43

23988222.description: Track workout with John Davis. Set up a video camera to capture our form. 10 x 400m with full lap recovery. Splits: 82, 79, 76, 75, 77, 77, 75, 78, 78, 79
23988222.title: Track 10 x 400m

20790143.description: Not a bad average pace considering I stopped to walk a few times. I think my new gait pattern is helping. Head is still congested.
20790143.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

34943398.title: Hawthorne Trail
34943398.description: Warm an uncomfortable but the strong breeze provided some cooling on the way back.

17441190.description: How could I not run fast on such a rare, nice cool evening?  Felt really good about 40 minutes in.  Finished with a big surge up the hill by West Side Park (31st Drive).  I'm ready for the race on Friday.
17441190.title: VFF tempo run

32870373.description: Sick yesterday, feeling a bit better today.
32870373.title: campus C loop

13318347.description: Found a new trail today.  First run in New Balance Minimus Zero MT00 trail shoes.  Very lightweight. Ample protection from trail debris and roots. Zero Drop (no raised heel). Good traction on grass, sandy or leaf-strewn trails. A great shoe!  Wore sockless, no issues.  Still need to give them a long trail run at San Felasco to put them through their paces, but I'm confident enough in them that I'll be using them at Trail of Payne.
13318347.title: Single track Hogtown Creek and Loblolly Woods

32349424.description: Nice and easy on a beautiful warm day.
32349424.title: easy campus

22034690.description: Very warm, didn't do much warmup. Have a few tight spots in my muscles (calves, thigh) from all the high intensity running lately.
22034690.title: warm up and down

33791226.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
33791226.description: Went back to bed this morning to catch some more rest and was actually able to sleep for a couple extra hours. In general felt good and fresh today. First two miles were 8 min. pace, then picked it up in tempo run style. Foot felt fine. Some quirks remaining around shins and knees (could be lingering from mileage buildup or just from *not* running much this week), and quads / hams / glutes from physical therapy.

23610406.title: no sidewalks
23610406.description: At least one of the foot bridges I use on this route were washed out. Legs were still fairly sore and stiff (especially at the start).

8090563.description: Really stiff this morning and still some soreness from the last run a few days ago.  Ran a short stretch on the roughest road I have been able to locate (stones embedded in asphalt). Bending the knees I was able to handle this just fine.
8090563.title: barefoot morning run

24048776.description: Good group!  I added some extra miles before and after. Legs were tired and it was sloppy humid so perceived effort was high.
24048776.title: Lloyd Clarke Sports group run

2862235.description: I'm a horrible swimmer so after a while I decided to get out of the pool and run.
2862235.title: swim and barefoot run

11787636.title: San Felasco
11787636.description: It feels like a long time since I have run at San Felasco. Decided to wear my Altra Lone Peak trail shoes. Ran the blue loop with a diversion along the dirt roads under the power lines and along the outside perimeter of the park.  These were a nice find since they actually have some hills. Not sure of distance.

18624751.title: Work to Morningside Nature Center
18624751.description: Anyone know the actual distance of the outer loop (blue blazes) at Morningside?  The map says 3 miles but I think it must be shorter, I don't believe I was moving that fast. I'm happy to report that today I ran this route 15 minutes faster than last week. It's still warm out there mid-day, I didn't carry any water or have any water stops.
