I'm digging these Tuesday daytime runs from work since it gives me another day each week of running in daylight.

16292950.description: Hot and humid.  Ran this race faster last year... barefoot.  Went out a little faster than I should have but really I just wasn't ready to race today. A lot of good runners there. So many race-day registrations that they ran out of numbers.  Mile splits: 5:48, 6:38, 7:23.
16292950.title: Melon Run Meh

8451308.description: Stiff this morning, legs did not want to bend, had trouble finding my form.  Ran on some rooty, rocky, and rough surfaces today.
8451308.title: barefoot - increasing distance

18292563.description: Dog Days 5k race. The first two miles were at a good pace, even with the big 8th Ave hill, but I guess the inclines got to me.  My time was just a few seconds off my previous best 5k from April. I was not able to push myself into that next level of pain.  Placed 5th overall and won my age group. I wish I had been able to fend off the people who passed me in mile three. Splits: 5:36, 5:43, 6:28, 0:32 (Time 18:19 and avg. 5:54 per mile).
18292563.title: Dog Days 5k

34808267.title: Rain Run
34808267.description: Cold. Wet. Nasty. Awesome! Except for the chafing. That is not awesome.

31361534.title: Quadbuster - San Felasco trails
31361534.description: In one word... Conquistador! Lots of ups and downs. Today was my first long run in Topo Oterro shoes and I think I have found my "heavy duty" long distance trail shoe. Great day on the trails.

13840741.description: Flatwoods 5k race in the Austin Carey Memorial Forest. A really nice race venue on a flat course, close to town, with excellent event organization.  1st in my age group and 2nd overall.  Splits:  6:05, 6:09, 6:17, 0:34.  Wore my NB Minimus Trail Zero which were really great for this packed limestone roadway with loose bits here and there. I feel like I'm getting into race shape.
13840741.title: Flatwoods 5k

5094338.title: Too gorgeous to wear shoes
5094338.description: Sunny and 70 degrees, could not bring myself to put on shoes.  Felt great except the feet are a little soft and tender from so many weeks without any barefoot work.

35496586.title: caught in the rain
35496586.description: Cold stormfront came through during the run. Caught on the Hawthorne trail. Survived and enjoyed the coldness!

2881622.description: Finished the route barefoot after taking off my VFF.  Felt pretty fast. Even though my feet were soaked, the bottoms of my feet held up pretty well.  I'm considering running a 5k race barefoot.

21502379.title: 8th Ave short flat
21502379.description: This body wants to run. I had to cut it short to get the kids ready for school. Added one 8th Ave hill.

24170236.title: morning
24170236.description: Boom. 50 mile week. Tired for sure.

18837017.description: Longest run of my whole life! Wasn't feeling perfect, I had some stomach distress yesterday and this morning probably due to some "unusual" famers' market greens I ate yesterday. Took fuel along (mostly honey). I guess it helped, but I still hit a wall at mile 20. Legs just quit, couldn't lift them. It also warmed up a lot by the time I shuffled in a smidge before noon. Thought I was running easy for the first half but maybe still going too fast (mostly 8 minute miles with a few faster sections which should be alright since my breathing was easy the whole time, but now I'm less confident about my target marathon race pace). Marathoners are CRAZY for running that far. ;)  Tested race day equipment: RaceReady shorts with pockets, Inov-8 Bare-X Lite 150, gel containers, and my Florida Track Club singlet. Also carried water but I won't do that on race day.
18837017.title: near marathon distance

2965624.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

2897353.description: Did the outside loop, blue then yellow.  The sandy spots were damp / packed and didn't give me much trouble.  Three long days in a row... this dog is tired.
2897353.title: San Felasco Hammock Preserve trails (off Millhopper Rd)

28173030.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back
28173030.description: Low effort. Felt good. Training the neuromuscular pathways...

33306628.description: Very warm. Pushed the 2nd mile and then kind of fell apart. Legs still sore from workouts this week. A good workout even if not race quality performance.
33306628.title: Tipple's Third Thursday Beer Run

20248820.description: Short tempo on the Waldo Road bike path.
20248820.title: short tempo Waldo Road bike path

35103337.description: Moderate pace. Coolish but humid morning. Nice run!
35103337.title: Bacon Strip 11

4845467.description: Felt nice and smooth.  Glutes and hips were sore from the PT earlier in the week.  Core is still weak, hard to hold my hips in position for the entire run.  First 30 minutes was spot-on though.

35400000.title: Hawthorne Trail
35400000.description: post-rain sunshine humid bath. Calves sore from yesterday.

12985205.description: Ran the powerline and park border trails.  There are some nice hills on the powerline trails. I got turned around trying to get back to the trail head, everything crosses at strange angles, so I ran a little further than I wanted to.  Used Runstar free on my phone to get GPS distance.
12985205.title: San Felasco powerline roads

8732924.title: Heat acclimation run
8732924.description: Wore two long sleeve shirts, running pants, socks and shoes to encourage heat acclimation. I have not been able to run in over a week (wife out of town) so it felt good to get out there.

36397675.title: Gate2Gate Trail Run 25k
36397675.description: Couldn't have asked for a nicer day for the inaugural Gate2Gate Trail Run. I ran the 25k and earned a 2nd place finish. Will be happy to take some time off to heal the bod.

2886862.title: Greenway to University turn at Swamp
2886862.description: Morning run before breakfast.  Hopefully burned some fat. Didn't have much lift today after running last night, took a lot of effort to keep moving.  Where is "Humid" in Weather?

13485720.description: 10 x stadium stairs with no rest.  I usually run them faster like intervals with rest in between, this time I went slower but kept continuous motion.  Foot hurting so I picked this workout to get good cardio without pounding.  This is my last real workout before the race next weekend, so hopefully I can baby myself all week and be ready to go.
13485720.title: Stadium stairs at the Swamp

31756708.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

18010896.title: easy hour on the greenways
18010896.description: Must be sick. Joins are achy, pressure behind my eyes, sore muscles. Luckily I don't have any severe symptoms (like a raging head cold).

36018368.title: Track ladder - 1-2-3-4-3-2 laps
36018368.description: Track workout - Ladder 1-2-3-4-3-2 laps. I had to add in extra rest after the second 1200m and cut it short after the 800m in order to finish the workout, we started at an aggressive pace and I was completed gassed. Splits: 1:17, 2:44, 4:22, 6:12, ?, 2:51

26624222.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
26624222.description: Chilly with slight drizzle. Perfect for running.

1993425.description: Ran barefoot part of the way, some on hot concrete.  Near-instant blisters.  Eagerly waiting for my RunAmocs to arrive from Soft Star Shoes.
1993425.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway

5461904.title: Morning run in huaraches
5461904.description: Gotta be my longest run in huaraches.  Mixed sidewalks and greenway trail.  Seemed difficult to "run lightly" today.  Maybe I'm not a morning person when it comes to running.  Got a little blister on my left foot (that's new!) and a little strap rub on the top of the right foot.  Next time I'll try Injinji socks with them.

30957116.description: Steep hill sprints are key to training the glutes to engage. Cruised like a missile after doing my hill sprints. My first pair of VFF are just about ready for the dumpster (just crossed 300 miles and 4 years old, these have always had an issue where the upper was separating from the sole. I will not shoe goo them again).
30957116.title: campus

34983545.description: Brad Hudson's 10k spec test. 4 x 2k at 10k pace, 1 x 1k hard, with 400m (3 min) recoveries. Crushed it. Hovered near 6 minute per mile pace for the 2k reps, finished the last interval at fast 5k pace. Splits: 7:36, 7:34, 7:32, 7:29, 3:26
34983545.title: Track workout 10k spec test

34825314.description: Nice trail run at San Felasco. Took no fuel during the run. Last 5.5 miles at 7:40 pace (hardest effort where I could keep my breathing under control). Getting close to taper time, this was my last long in prep for Five Points. Had to pad and tape my feet before this run due to raw spots from earlier in the week. That worked fine, no real pain issues and the tape stayed in place, plenty of room in Altra Lone Peak for the bandage.
34825314.title: San Felasco trails

27771845.title: Track strides
27771845.description: One mile stride the straights on the track.

34047430.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

30422535.description: Feeling beat up from 3 hours of singletrack mountain biking yesterday. First run in Altra Olympus maximal cushion shoes. They had good grip on the sandy greenway trails near my house, handled roots and rocks with ease. Were fine on pavement, too.
30422535.title: first run in Altra Olympus shoes

32405047.description: Threw in a couple long hill strides. Very warm today.
32405047.title: campus

2477994.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
2477994.description: One of the guys decided to rabbit us today and we all died hard.

19700446.description: Just a short run to get warmed up and generate some blood flow.  After the marathon I had some serious acute pain on the outside of my hip. That has subsided and now I can feel the general muscle soreness everywhere else.
19700446.title: The Daily

19511438.title: morning miles
19511438.description: Up early this morning so I went a few extra miles on my way to and from the track. This takes my Altra Samsons over 200 miles and they are still in good shape.

13485648.description: Clock time includes the stadium stairs.
13485648.title: Swamp stadium roundtrip

31577777.title: Hilly San Felasco Trails
31577777.description: First run in Inov-8 TrailRoc 235. Great shoes! Good protection, no cushion. Upper is snug to the foot without being tight. No blisters or rubbing. Ran parking lot to parking lot with 2 x Conquistador in the middle. Nice cool day. Trails were in good shape day after Tour de Felasco MTB and I mostly had them to myself. Forgot to charge my phone last night so I'm guessing at pace/distance. Meant to eat something mid-run but I forgot that, too. This caps off a 60 mile week.

14447450.description: Very easy pace to get out the stiffness and soreness from yesterday's 22 miler.
14447450.title: The Daily

23774136.title: Swamp stadium Bull Gator statue roundtrip

30675098.title: work day run
30675098.description: One notch above shuffle pace. I wasn't sure why I was so tired and then I remembered that on top of the 16 miles I ran yesterday I also mountain biked 19 miles. Bright sunny happy day, though.

11024604.description: WARM.  Had a headache all day.  I think I had too many carbs yesterday.  Felt good to get a run in despite the heat.
11024604.title: University Ave 6mi loop

18159961.title: no sidewalks
18159961.description: Greenway side trails had some mud puddles that required slow navigation.

11189226.description: Beautiful day for a barefoot run!
11189226.title: 39th Ave Loop

29889630.description: Track workout on tired legs. 5 x 1000m.  Interval times add up to an 18:33 5k which is way slower than I want to be. Managed a hard kick on the last one. Splits (recovery): 3:44 (1:58), 3:39 (2:19), 3:41 (1:47), 3:50 (3:26), 3:39
29889630.title: Track intervals 5 x 1000m

6714060.title: Happy Easter
6714060.description: Acclimate... acclimate... acclimate... Gotta get used to this heat.

20441857.description: Ran with John doing his routine. We put our shoes back on after one round of barefoot strides (Cold!).  I did a 400m time trial in 64 seconds, which is an improvement of 5 seconds over my last time trial.  Getting faster!
20441857.title: easy running, drills, and 400m time trial

9597198.title: San Felasco outer loop
9597198.description: Foiled by foot fail.  Blister on the inside of the big toe.

34912810.title: shake-out
34912810.description: Included some walking, loosening up, and MP. Had terrible headache last night and in the middle of the night, so not the solid night of sleep I was hoping for. Headache still with me this morning. :(

24951761.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

3741883.title: Painted wall thru campus
3741883.description: Great pace.  Started sore around the achilles.  I've been neglecting my eccentric strength exercises. First time running past the painted wall.  Pretty happy with this run.

22673902.description: Still sore from Thursday. Good run with Hutson, Stephanie, and Dan C.
22673902.title: San Felasco trails

3083874.description: It is a lot of fun running barefoot on trails! This was a huge milestone for me.  Thanks Cathy B. for going slower today which allowed me to do this run.  Calves were still sore and tired from yesterday's 5k race. No major injuries from trail debris or tree roots. I had to remove a tiny thorn from my heel and I hit a rock or something that really hurt for a while. It was very hard to keep up the cadence and lift towards the end, so I was landing heavier on my whole foot than I wanted.  The feet and calves are sore.  My knees feel great, though.
3083874.title: 10 miles barefoot - San Felasco mountain bike trails

35010010.title: Race the Tortoise 5k
35010010.description: Great weather for Race the Tortoise 5k race. Executed my race plan well, kept my breathing under control, finished with a strong kick... which I needed to beat the amazing 11 year old girl who I raced beside almost the whole way. Finish time 18:10. Splits: 5:47, 6:03, 5:49, 35s. Won 1st male Masters, 2nd overall.

31458693.description: Felt great. Perfect weather (cool with breeze and occasional mist / drizzle).
31458693.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

10795984.title: barefoot on a cold and blustery day
10795984.description: Barefoot run through the neighborhood.  Chilly with a slight drizzle.

2392874.title: Yay for shoes.
2392874.description: Going to cut back on the barefoot and minimalist shoes for a bit.  My feet are just not ready to go minimalist full-time.  I ran in Nike Frees tonight and the things went well.  Pain-free, slow, but well.

28897901.description: Longer than usual run before I hit the track for 800m of sprinting straights. Completed 6 x steep hill sprints on the way home. My Altra Samsons have over 500 miles on them today and are finally starting to show some wear.
28897901.title: Track sprints and hill sprints

34909848.title: greenways
34909848.description: No bridges slowed me down. Did some fartlek-type work towards the end.

5870530.title: Brywood hills
5870530.description: Just around my neighborhood.  A good week of running.  No injuries.  Looking forward to Trail of Payne next weekend.

4605544.title: shake out run
4605544.description: Trying to unwind the kinks from being in a car for 2 days.  My new heart rate monitor is really cool.

21896267.title: Track workout 5 x 1000m
21896267.description: A warm rainy morning with lots of peeps showing up at the track. 5 x 1000m with 400m jog recovery. Splits: 3:54, 3:32, 3:27, 3:30, 3:29  (per mile pace range 6:16 - 5:33). Not feeling flat any longer. :)

6994801.title: barefoot on the beach
6994801.description: The cool ocean water felt better after going for a run on the beach.

15477709.description: 4 x hill repeats. 1:58,1:56,1:54,1:57. I took (and needed) less rest between these, I just jogged back and started again.  Previously when doing this workout I felt that I needed to walk a bit.
15477709.title: one-third mile hill repeats

18182539.title: Lloyd Clarke Sports group run with my kids
18182539.description: Sunday night Lloyd Clarke Sports group run. I took the kids and we ended up walking most of it. They spent a lot of energy running around and acting crazy before the run actually began. They liked getting splashed with water from my bottle and making them look all "sweaty". They also liked going out to dinner afterwards. Could be the start of a nice Sunday night tradition.

6201287.description: Except for the barf burp, felt nice.
6201287.title: barefoot greenway and neighborhood

21759966.description: Took a while to warm up and get loose (back a little stiff from sleeping on a guest room bed), but felt good after about 40 minutes in.
21759966.title: around

36528932.description: 20 minute run then 10 x 1 minute "on", 1 minute "off". Felt good towards the end and pushed a little which I am now regretting because my piriformis is very angry and yelling at me.  1000 miles on my original Altra Samsons.
36528932.title: Track workout 1 minute on 1 minute off

3636023.title: John Holmes 16 mile trail race barefoot
3636023.description: I finished!  Longest run ever in my whole life. Barefoot is the way to go when running on sugary sand trails.  Third in my age group.  First half of the race I was at the back of the lead pack.  I died hard hard hard after 1 hour 50 minutes... for some reason I thought I should try to race the second (last) 7-mile loop. My shoulders and back tied in knots.  After the race, lots of people were interested in my bare feet... maybe I'll make the highlight reel. A Gainesville woman (Kristen Bryant) won the female side of our age group.

23575667.description: Great workout with John Davis. 2 x 1600m (6:13, 6:18), 2 x 800m (3:02, 3:00).  We took a little more rest in between than originally planned (whole lap instead of 60s). I added 2 x 400m on the end (1:11, 1:12).
23575667.title: Track workout

3420742.description: Had some tightness in my ankles during the night.  Didn't sleep well.  A morning run seemed like just the thing to loosen up the lower legs.  Doing a double today, running with Matt C. on campus after work.  Trying to balance eating less to lose weight with needing to put fuel in the tank.  Today will be a hearty meal day to make sure I can replenish and rebuild.
3420742.title: University Ave 6mi loop

34435976.description: Nice group trail run at San Felasco from Millhopper Rd. entrance to the north side entrance (gate to gate). Included a little search and rescue to make sure everyone made it back ok.
34435976.title: San Felasco Trails

34866786.description: Ran the first half of FPoL course with Richard G.
34866786.title: FPoL course

23229203.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
23229203.description: The humidity felt good on my eyes.

21301283.title: work to Morningside
21301283.description: Beautiful day but warmed up quickly. A good day to start working on the tan. :) Ran to Morningside Nature Center and did two outer loops.

35832534.description: Another fasted long run. Heat kind of got to me towards the end even though it wasn't actually so hot yet.
35832534.title: South Walnut Creek hike and bike

35367589.description: Ran to a fitness area and did pull-ups, push-ups, dips, etc.
35367589.title: campus

16152352.title: run to MIT
16152352.description: I cannot get over the density of colleges and universities in Boston!

30163878.title: San Felasco trail tempo
30163878.description: Trail tempo for 19:26. I think this is my fastest time on this route.

13266358.title: Swamp stadium roundtrip
13266358.description: Time includes the stadium stair repeats.

4195410.description: Wore the Adidas Kanadias which are pretty heavy, they definitely affect my stride... kind of like ankle weights, I guess.  Total for the day was 17.8 miles.
4195410.title: San Felasco outer loop

6930516.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
6930516.description: Legs and feet were stiff. Very nice cool morning.

5331735.title: Cupid Fun Run 5k
5331735.description: Got 2nd place overall!  Did ok following my race plan, but didn't feel completely great this morning.  Ended up chatting with the guy who won through most of the race.  It turns out that sub-7 minute mile pace is not "conversational pace" for me, especially when running up that hill by the fraternities... that's where the winner dropped me.

27844152.description: Rainy. Tripped on uneven sidewalk and bashed my arm and lower back on a concrete bench.  I lucked out, didn't hit anything too hard and the crash didn't affect the rest of the run.
27844152.title: rainy

6464964.description: I cannot explain it but running in the Altra Instincts seem to be curing me of my Achilles pain.  This morning was my third run in them.  Nagging injury for the last six months is disappearing in a week since getting the new shoes.
6464964.title: Altra Instincts cure Achilles Tendinitis?

24908207.title: training lows
24908207.description: After pretty much OD'ing on office doughnuts yesterday, and then staying up late working on my web site, I bailed on my plan for a 4am long run. I am not sure I am enjoying these long slogging miles.

4028717.description: Should have probably only gone 4 miles, but it is hard to stop once I go to all the trouble of getting on my gear and making it sweaty.  Muscles remembered at mile 6 that they were still microtorn/whatever from the recent half marathon.
4028717.title: trying some new routes

17006779.description: Barefoot. Ran with my buddy Matt C.
17006779.title: Tipple's beer happy hour run

30390240.description: Long progression run. If not in pace, definitely in effort.  Finished the last two miles at 7:34 pace. OMG tired.
30390240.title: long progression

29261687.title: moderate progressive in heat
29261687.description: Heat didn't seem to bother me. Felt good but didn't push hard, just let myself cruise. I did stop to look at a couple of snakes.

26021049.title: rain run
26021049.description: Some trail, some sidewalk. Got to break out my VFF due to the rain.

35193095.description: Bummed that I didn't find out a race was cancelled today until I was turned away at the gate. When I got home, I didn't even take off my bib number before heading out into the rain. Turned into a very nice run on the greenways, perfect temp with light rain. Alternated easy and tempo paces along the levees for about 21:30 total time at tempo pace.
35193095.title: rain run levee tempo

4881003.title: 23rd Blvd to University
4881003.description: Needed to burn off the three varieties of beer soup I made yesterday, plus pancakes for breakfast today.  Running can be a thing of beauty... I had about 10 minutes of completely effortless running. Able to maintain proper form for a bit longer this time.  Would have had better pace overall if I hadn't bonked hard at the end... oh man my GLUTES!  Rainy but turned out to be a great day to run.  T-shirt and shorts were perfect.

32084175.title: incline repeats x 5
32084175.description: Incline repeats .7 miles each on SW 2nd Ave near the golf course (NW 34th St. to Village Dr.). Allergies! Between tree pollen and grass clippings and leaf blower dust... but otherwise it's a nice wide new sidewalk for running repeats. Splits: 4:26, 4:25, 4:18, 4:18, 4:15 (6:20 - 6:04 per mile pace)

35916905.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

14328523.description: Legs still feeling the Wednesday evening race.  Hopefully will be in good shape for tomorrow morning's race.
14328523.title: nice cool morning

28869641.title: 8th Ave short flat
28869641.description: Hot and sunny. Breaking in new pair of Inov-8 Bare-X Lite 150 shoes (my third pair even though I have not worn out the previous ones). These are red, white and blue, perfect for the local 4th of July race.

21487846.title: Waldo Road
21487846.description: Sadly my headache returned after I stopped running.

31294817.description: Also added a couple of steep hill sprints. My quad still has a little hitch in it from the MTB crash but otherwise felt pretty good.
31294817.title: cold morning

19276645.title: Turkey Trot 10k
19276645.description: Lloyd Clarke Sports put on a good race today. The weather was perfect. I improved over last year's race by 43 seconds and since I ran smarter this year, the race was so much more enjoyable. Finished 1st in my age group with a time of 39:44. The plan was to go out under control, just try to stay nice and smooth. I think I executed well, felt strong through the 2nd half of the race, crushed mile 5, had a great finish kick. Splits: 6:20, 6:37, 6:36, 6:34, 6:10, 6:17, 1:10

16901789.description: Group run at Austin Cary Memorial Forest, fun as always!
16901789.title: group run at Austin Cary Memorial Forest

27242895.description: On the track for 1 mile of stride straights jog curves. 6 x stadium stairs. Long gradual uphill surge on the run back home.
27242895.title: Variety

17309322.title: Track workout 6x800m
17309322.description: Great workout with John D. and Meredith. I had some aches and pains in the foot, calf, shin, ....  certainly due to the recent intensity increases. Tried to run these quick but relaxed (no sprinting!).  6 x 800m repeats with 400m jog recovery in between (aiming for 2 minute recover but mostly we were close to 3 minutes on the jog lap). Splits: 3:08, 3:09, 3:00, 2:59, 2:58, 2:50

6997235.description: Really bad eating weekend.  Fish and Chips twice.  Hamburger and fries twice.  Ice cream at least three times.  A few beers. Started this run about 6 pounds heavy.  Time to get back on the healthy eating wagon.
6997235.title: too... many... french fries

35770490.title: bike path
35770490.description: warm. I think I am beginning to *hate* cushioned shoes.

10141290.title: Moc3 fartleks
10141290.description: Since my 5k time has pretty much plateaued with my training consisting of mostly slow easy mileage, it is time to increase the intensity and start doing some speed work. Three Fartleks in Moc3.  Started out great.  But... over the course of this run I got cramps in both arches, pain in my right big toe, and pain in the front of my hip that made me slow down and cut the run shorter than planned.

19583067.description: I don't think I've been puddle jumping since college. Nice rainy run for muddin' in my New Balance Minimus MT00. Stayed on the greenway trails until it got too dark to see.
19583067.title: Rain Run!

28538100.description: Sore and tired legs. Did 2 x 5 min hard effort along the top of the levees. My old trail gloves were super slippery on the wet boardwalks.
28538100.title: greenways and levees

13106961.description: Very warm this morning!  It was 70 degrees when I walked out the door at 5:30am.
13106961.title: warm morning

15593421.title: night run
15593421.description: Started out and then had to walk a bit to let the Chinese food settle. Felt light-headed early on a few times, my body was apparently still busy digesting. I didn't carry any water, had one water stop on campus around mile 10. When the breeze was blowing it was actually not bad, but generally I was hot and drenched. The new running form is working my glutes and lower back muscles.

2122650.title: VFF Bikilas!
2122650.description: Had to try the new VFF Bikila shoes I bought today.  Only downside so far is that they make my toes really hot!  Since I was at Lloyd Clarke Sports I also tried the Newtons.  They were very interesting shoes, felt great, like I could run a ton of miles on them... but also seemed like they would let my form go lazy.  $150 for the entry level Newton seems like too much money.

35166624.title: Track workout 3 x 800m, 1 x 1200m, strides
35166624.description: Track workout 3 x 800m, 1 x 1200m (pacing Richard), strides. 800m splits: 2:55, 2:57, 2:51  1200m split: 5:00.  Not feeling great today, legs have some quirks around the knees.

27481776.title: barefoot through campus
27481776.description: I now have tender feet, but kept the pace low and didn't tear any holes in my soles.

20400104.description: Out/Back route. Strong headwind on the way out. Splits: 9:44, 8:57
20400104.title: tempo run on Waldo Rd. bike path

30113586.title: Track Birthday Mile
30113586.description:
In honor of August birthdays, Betsy and I raced a Mile on the track, both of us hoping to go under 5 minutes. I took us out just a little fast on the first lap and even though I thought I was pushing lap 3 it was still slow. We finished in 5:13 which is still not bad for this newly minted "Masters" runner. Splits: 1:12 (including the "extra" distance at the start), 1:19, 1:21, 1:20.

Proper pacing is hard, and the Mile is a distance that requires specific training for optimal performance. Maybe next year!

13776368.description: Had to take time off from work for a couple appointments so I squeezed some miles in during lunch time. Very warm today despite the breeze.
13776368.title: no sidewalks

23022777.title: short round trip UF track
23022777.description: plus another mile on the track.

35454399.title: Long on Hawthorne Trail
35454399.description: Turned into a real slog fest.

20597343.title: Swamp Stadium Stairs
20597343.description: Felt like I needed to do something else after the track workout, so I went to the stadium to do four hard sprints bottom to top on the stairs. Ascent splits: 46, 44, 43, 43 (seconds)

2356130.title: Good to be running again.
2356130.description: Slow run in my huarache sandals, looking over the hazards on the Melon Run course.   Trying to decide whether to run tomorrow or spectate, and what to wear on my feet.

34565902.description: Felt great! Amazing what some cool temps will do for perceived effort.
34565902.title: cold morning

24785450.description: Long run in the books.  Didn't carry any water or fuel, just used water stops and chugged one bottle of Gatorade about half way through. Weighed 5 pounds lighter afterward so I definitely got behind on my intake.
24785450.title: 25 mile long run

34533144.description: Cold and windy with cold rain. Numb hands! Included two long (about 3/4 of a mile) hill repeats: 4:45, 4:33
34533144.title: Long hill repeats

5825743.title: First run in NB Minimus Road
5825743.description: Too early to tell how these shoes will do for me.  I think I may have bought a half size too small.  My feet drifted up towards the toes a little bit, making the shoe feel smaller than when I tried it at the store.  I had to take off my thick socks.  Felt ok sockless.  The raised heel definitely affects my foot landing, we'll see if I can adjust. Better for me than Nike Free for sure, though.

22621210.description: Hard SPEED workout from the mind of Dan C. who luckily let me draft the whole way.  We had an extra 200m at the beginning with extra rest since an additional runner showed up we started over, but otherwise short rest in between.  Splits: 3 x 200m (35, 35, 36), 2 x 300m (52, 54), 2 x 400m (1:17, 1:17), 2 x 300m (57, 55), 2 x 200m (34, 34)
22621210.title: Track workout short ladder

17066619.title: Trail run at Alafia River State Park
17066619.description: Hot, intense trail run in the middle of the day at Alafia River State Park near Tampa, FL.  My Altra Lone Peaks were perfect shoes for the mix of terrain that included mud, steep humps, roots, and rocks. Crazy twisty and rocky single track trails like the Rock Garden and Moonscape made me glad I had my serious trail shoes. The GPS on my phone crashed partway through (must have been all the turns and twists!), I'm not sure how far I actually went.

7607990.title: GHFC round trip
7607990.description: Still do not like NB Minimus Road.  However, they remind me that I need to "run light", something I was cheating on in my Altra Instincts.

34960849.title: one-third mile hill repeats
34960849.description: Started faster than planned. Cut the workout after 4 reps since I am supposed to be in marathon recovery. Splits: 1:52, 1:54, 1:50, 1:47

4478840.description: VFF and Barefoot.  The Bikilas continue to want to rub a raw spot on the inside of my feet just above the arches... took them off and carried them before too much damage was done.
4478840.title: Harris Branch

36210621.title: morning
36210621.description: Felt a touch cooler this morning. Did a long walk warmup before starting this run.

15519557.description: New Shoes! First run in Merrell Trail Gloves. I like them so far. Picked them up on sale locally.
15519557.title: Brywood hills

12634173.description: Busted ribs suck. They are definitely healing up but still not quite ready.  The pain was bad enough that I decided to turn around and head for home after about a mile.  It's a drag this happened during prime training / racing season.
12634173.title: busted ribs suck

13299381.description: Decided to do another loop.  Felt pretty good.
13299381.title: Brywood hills

9366461.description: To and from The Swamp plus 8 x stadium stairs.  Some walking on the way home.
9366461.title: Swamp Stadium stairs

33865456.title: warm up and down to track

17352212.title: 8th Ave short flat
17352212.description: Barefoot to bring everything back into check and keep the injuries away.

21041293.description: After spending a few hours in the crawl space under our house, I was already a mess so I decided to take a short jog.  Dust and mold not making my nose and lungs happy.
21041293.title: very short greenway jog

9874861.title: greenway and singletrack
9874861.description: First run after being sick, the crud is still lingering.  Took it nice and easy.  Going through all of my shoes again, trying to decide on my fall racing shoes.  Today was MWU3. Considering the MWU4 which has a crazy color scheme.

35236453.title: progression
35236453.description: I was just going to go easy because I woke up tight and stiff but then ran into Hutson R. and Mark O. and jumped in with them (they were running faster). Eventually felt warmed up so I continued to increase the pace on my solo return home.

34242639.description: Tom Walker Half Marathon race. Faded badly but still pulled out an age group win. Legs feeling deep fatigue. Splits: 6:15, 6:20, 6:22, 6:09, 6:23, 6:25, 6:38, 6:36, 6:36, 7:03, 7:13, 7:14, 7:06, 35s
34242639.title: Tom Walker Half Marathon

6679883.title: totally awful
6679883.description: Just felt terrible.  I'm sure the heat was a contributor.  Also notice some commonalities with the last time I felt bad running after work... I skipped my Workrave again, sitting in my chair all day.  So bad my back hurt getting up to go each lunch and again at the end of the day.  Sitting is baaaaad, mmm-kay?  Also had a huge Chipotle burrito for lunch. Need to eat smaller lunch and maybe have an afternoon snack instead of suffering the big bloat.  Oh yeah, and I didn't have afternoon coffee like usual.

14975196.description: Nice cool morning after a hard rain last evening. I was a little stiff in the legs this morning and the feet are tender from yesterday's runs so I went nice and easy.  Went longer than my normal Daily just to get in a little more recovery pace.
14975196.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway

26373204.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

22873855.description: Still feeling twiginess in the glute.  Getting almost a full day of standing at work should help.
22873855.title: The Daily

33519848.description: Tired after hours of SUP over the weekend.
33519848.title: campus A loop

28395488.description: Steep hill sprints. 4 x 8th Ave, 2 x 23rd Street (steep!). 1 mile of straight sprints on the track. This is part of the Introductory phase as described by Brad Hudson in "Run Faster".
28395488.title: Steep hill sprints and track

20072401.description: Experiment over, my body does *NOT* like complete rest / idleness. After going about a quarter mile I could feel my body saying "thank you" and a lot of tension releasing. You are welcome, body.  You're welcome.
20072401.title: Waldo Road greenway

35888478.title: San Felasco trails
35888478.description: Got out early to pick up some miles before the group run. Felt tired.

30733833.description: Nice run with Patrick's training group and some other running buds. For me this was some much-needed recovery LSD. Lots of Ultra running talk making me eager to try another 50k.
30733833.title: San Felasco trails

33453882.title: University Ave 6mi loop
33453882.description: After a weekend of Stand-Up Paddleboard (SUP) fishing. My Core was tired! Nice and cool after the evening rain.

24349686.title: heat training
24349686.description: Sweatpants and long sleeves.  A lot of horrible smells in the air today. Between roadkill, smelly spilled garbage, and the heat training it was not my favorite running experience.

8886463.title: no sidewalks
8886463.description: Part 2 of a double. My brain and body seemed to remember the "run light" pattern from this morning's barefoot run so I felt good in my cushioned Altra Instincts.  Still hot out there but the breeze helped.

11173135.description: Altra Adam is a great addition to my minimalist shoe arsenal.  Ground feel is about the same as VFF but no toe pockets.  Saw a river otter on this run.
11173135.title: First run in Altra Adams

34855723.description: Beautiful sunny day for barefoot run! Temps in the high 60s. Also... shoes are rubbing my raw spots so barefoot is better!
34855723.title: barefoot on campus

31739427.title: campus run
31739427.description: Left ankle still sore. Legs still tired but maybe a little better.

19432747.title: Tom Walker Half Marathon
19432747.description: A great Tom Walker Memorial Half Marathon experience. Legs were still a little tired and sore from Thursday's track workout but I crushed a new PR anyway. Beat my previous half marathon best by 3:47 with a 1:26:04. This is a *lifetime* best! THANK YOU to the pace group that pulled me through the first half of the race. I left it all out on the course today. Splits: 6:36, 6:55, 6:43, 6:40, 6:42, 6:55, 6:33, 6:17, 6:26, 6:18, 6:36, 6:21, 6:19, :36

9893864.title: greenway and singletrack
9893864.description: Today I tested Soft Star RunAmoc DASH to compare to MWU3 on the same route.  The DASH vibram trail sole definitely has the best traction on sugary sand compared to anything else I've run in.

24233908.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

23199666.title: 8th Ave short flat
23199666.description: These Altra Instincts have over 300 miles on them.

36046974.description: Ran one loop with Richard, then went slower for a bit, then quick / at effort for the last 3.
36046974.title: San Felasco trails

6902215.description: Felt really short compared to the 20-miler I ran on Sunday.
6902215.title: Brywood hills

34289835.description: Light rain, nice day on the trails today.
34289835.title: San Felasco trails

27162793.description: Really great time of year to run the trails of San Felasco! This morning was foggy and cool. There were no bugs, no spiderwebs, and very few people! I was able to do some exploring of new (to me) trails and also ran some of my favorites such as Conquistador. Had a rough patch after 2.5 hours but ended up finishing the last 30 minutes hard. No calories in during the run, just a tiny bit of food before the run.  I estimated distance and pace recorded here.
27162793.title: San Felasco long run

16543868.description: Barefoot in the heat. This is an out-and-back route, I ran fast on the way back. Between the pace and the sidewalk heat, my feet are a little unhappy.
16543868.title: 8th Ave short flat

33731337.title: campus to Boulware springs
33731337.description: 2nd run of the day. Tired legs and burping Indian food.

31546345.title: progression run plus double tempo
31546345.description: First 9.3 miles in 1:11. Two tempo loops around Lake Alice (little over 3 miles each) in 20:32, 20:45 with 1 minute recovery, faster than 6:45 pace per mile. Hard day!

24030463.title: Stadium stairs
24030463.description: Full stairs bottom to top and back with no rest in between. Managed 8 reps before I quit. Wore long sleeves.

21230618.title: Race the Tortoise 5k
21230618.description: Age group PR, Age group winner, 2nd overall with a time of 18:07.  Cold morning was great for racing.  I'm excited to see what happens after I get some real training in with my new running technique. Splits: 5:39, 6:03, 6:25 (last 1.1 mile)

13341437.title: Greenways again
13341437.description: Second run in NB Minimus Trail Zero.  A Fun shoe.

36258597.description: Felt pretty good. Under 8-minute pace for first half of the run (before doing stadiums)
36258597.title: Bull Gator statue at Swamp Stadium roundtrip

28886478.title: Hot mid-day run on campus
28886478.description: Hot and sunny. Effort level was definitely progressive and pushed a bit at the end.

32194771.title: GATE River Run 15k race
32194771.description: GATE River Run 15k race. 24th in age group, 204th male (out of 6773 male finishers). Interesting... if I had run a PR I could have been close to top 3 in my age group. Maybe next year!

15652252.title: no sidewalks
15652252.description: I love the smell of acetone (not ammonia) in the morning (aka fat burning / ketosis).

25397557.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

33851997.title: San Felasco trails
33851997.description: My NB Minimus MT00 are getting close to retirement (under 400 miles on them), I had forgotten how patched up they are (duck tape and shoe goo). I was still feeling good enough near the end of 14 miles that I wanted to run more, but tweaked the right foot again about a quarter mile before getting back to the trailhead. This time I felt the pain was just like a sprain (across the cuboid area). Decided to just call it a day. Thankfully seems to be no lingering effect after the run.

30936887.description: Group of four (Dan, Dan, Shawn, and Scott) ran "gate to gate" south side of San Felasco to the north side and back. Coooool morning, great run. Averaged 8 minutes per mile or faster (not including water stops).
30936887.title: San Felasco gate to gate

36231138.title: golf course sprints aka spectating XC
36231138.description: Spectating Mountain Dew Invitational XC meet. Running around on the gold course for around 3 miles. Very warm and humid by the last few races. Runners collapsing in dramatic fashion.

22237555.description: Stiff and sore after yesterday's effort.
22237555.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

16719337.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
16719337.description: First real run in a while, I hope I'm over whatever was dragging me down. It was OMG hot out there.  I need to research solutions to burning sweat in the eyes.

2309898.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
2309898.description: The rain scared off my running buddies so I was able to run slow and easy without any "man pressure" (TM).  Ran trails in my VFF, actually my first real run in them.  I'm glad I was not barefoot... due to the LIGHTNING! and the fact that the trail got really dark, especially with my glasses fogging up.  Bikilas have pretty good traction on wet boardwalk.  Listened to my body, no foot pain!  Icing now.

10423403.title: NB Minimus Road still suck
10423403.description: Had to stop and walk home after a quarter mile when I felt a twang from my ankle all the way up to my glute.  That's what I got for deciding to give the NB Minimus Road another try.  Switched to Soft Star Moc3 and everything was fine.

29832008.description: Ran one loop with Cathy B. then went back for trail tempo run in 21:22. These keep getting slower instead of faster!  I haven't run over 2 hours duration since April, so this was a good day of endurance building.
29832008.title: San Felasco Trail Tempo

3545626.title: warmup and cooldown for Dog Days

27747787.description: Warm!  Pollen count very high today.
27747787.title: greenway trails

31175340.description: Cold and windy day for the Pflugerville Pfeathered Pfun Run 10k. Two loops around Lake Pfleugerville on the crushed granite jogging path made a nice course. Won 1st overall in 36:28. Edit: course was short!
31175340.title: Pflugerville Pfeathered Pfun Run 10k

8270340.description: Calves were sore all week from the race.  They were better today before the run, but definitely sore again now!  The next skill for me to master is relaxing the calves.  I have no idea how to do this.  I think I'm done with my "rest" phase, ready to start doing some LSD endurance training.
8270340.title: long night loop

10612280.title: First run since injurious devil
10612280.description: Nice and easy in my Moc3.  Probably would have been better if I had not been stuffed full of food and beer.

2420042.description: Whew!  I'm tired now.  Ran in Nike Frees.  If you are still running in cotton t-shirts, go buy some Champion Duo-Dry at Target... seems to make a huge difference on these hot humid summer days.
2420042.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

7190222.description: This was a great workout.  Did a variation on my Brywood hill loop twice.  Got winded going up the hills, pushed over the top, and tried to recover while maintaining brisk pace on the downside.  No intervals this week. Still feeling Saturday's race I think.  Sore in the glutes, hips, and calves.  Pains in my knees, ankles, feet, and Achilles.  Loop splits: 26:45 / 23:53.  A cool 55 degrees when I started.
7190222.title: Brywood hills

3259999.description: My daughter is getting faster on her bike.  She's still in training wheels but I had to work to keep up on with her on the downhills.
3259999.title: running along with my daughter on her bike ride

28084974.description: I have been feeling off all week either due to allergies or switch to very low carb diet.  Included some short sprints. I have been wearing hat and gloves lately to try to help my body adapt to heat.
28084974.title: morning

33614446.title: campus
33614446.description: I know it was hot, but geeze that was awful. Very sluggish today.

10674735.title: Barefoot with work buds
10674735.description: Once again the barefoot run is just what I needed to bring everything back together.

28584763.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

15786378.title: early morning depletion run
15786378.description: Before breakfast. No fuel or water stops.  Altra Sampsons on my feet.

28191637.title: Track workout
28191637.description: Trying to work on STRENGTH ENDURANCE as Renato Canova would say. 2 x steep hill sprint, 1 mile of track stride straights jog curves, strides up to full sprint speed.  3 x 1600m with 400m of NOT jog pace recovery. Punctuated with hard 400m at the end. Splits (recovery) 1600m: 6:05 (1:51), 6:17 (1:56), 6:12. Split 400m: 1:12.  Tough workout.

19097443.description: Wasn't totally happy with the 5k this morning so I figured I would do a few more miles after I got home. Someone asked me after the race how the barefoot running was going and I realized it had been a long time since I went on an honest to goodness barefoot run.  Given the warm holiday weather, I decided to run barefoot. Out and back splits: 17:48, 13:47
19097443.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

34360885.title: campus C loop
34360885.description: Coolish breeze before the rain came and then finished in rain.

22534100.description: Fabulous cool morning and holy smokes we have sunshine again! Trails were in good shape and packed down from the rain. These "fast" long runs with Dan C. are going to do wonders for my fitness.
22534100.title: San Felasco trails

21337891.title: short round trip UF track
21337891.description: And some warmup laps around the track. COLD this morning.

13915154.description: Achilles tendons were really sore this morning.  Legs were tired and tight.  First long run on pavement in Altra Sampsons, not sure if that has anything to do with it.
13915154.title: 9 miler

23711830.title: Melon Run 3 mile race
23711830.description: Warm and humid morning! My best Melon Run performance yet in 17:41. Won my age group and brought home a nice watermelon to share with the family. Mile Splits: 6:28, 5:43, 5:31

33797277.description: Wore trail shoes and felt some pains in the top of my right foot (last week's injury) after hitting some uneven terrain.
33797277.title: San Felasco blue loop

1980554.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
1980554.description: Brand new shoes and this is what I get.

27918730.description: Included a few fast intervals across the top of the levee.
27918730.title: no sidewalks

33637272.title: campus with surges
33637272.description: Incline surges x 4 and decline surge x 1. Averaged 7 minute pace for the last 5 miles. Humid!

22917776.description: HOT!  Considering I was just feeling "ok" my pace was really good. Love the new shoes - Merrell Vapor Gloves. Good things to come.
22917776.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

3405188.title: long night loop
3405188.description: The moon was out bright tonight. My longest run in VFF. Definitely cooler.  Had plenty of fuel and actually let it digest before running... it was lasagna night at Leonardos (Millhopper).  I ran on major streets which were well-lit. Running in the upper end of my aerobic capacity for sure. I never stopped my watch during the run, so the overall time included all the stops. I had to take off my VFF and run barefoot for a few minutes to get rid of an arch cramp.  Getting them back on again took a while. And now I am drinking a beer because I earned it.

11964289.description: Soft Star Moc3 are still my favorite minimalist shoes.  It was cold this morning so I started running fast to get warmed up quickly and then decided not to slow down. lt feels good not to have any funny aches during and after a run.
11964289.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

3024845.description: Did a fast pick-up in the middle, pushed my friend Matt's distance up a little.  Went fast enough to feel it in the hamstrings.
3024845.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

8760166.description: Wow, seems like a really long time since I ran on the trails of San Felasco.  Did Blue plus Yellow outer loop barefoot.  Even though I turned into a wet soggy mess, I never felt too hot.  The heat acclimation run (long sleeves and pants) seems to be working to make a normal run like today feel nice and cool.
8760166.title: San Felasco trails outer loop barefoot

17219351.title: Swamp stadium stairs at noon
17219351.description: Wanted to get 20 minutes of stadium stairs. Managed 8 x stair repeats in a little over 20 minutes. It was HOT. This was good cardio but I had to walk a bit more in between reps than I planned. Altra Samsons are great for this kind of workout.

17903124.title: 9 miler
17903124.description: Finally a morning with a temperature I would describe as "cool"! Legs feeling pretty dead from last week's mileage and hard efforts. I had to patch my Moc3s with a little Shoe Goo last night, both outside edges of the sole (the secondary part, not the Vibram sole) starting to wear through. They have over 300 miles on them but this is a little disappointing. The upside is that there is no cushion to break down, so I ought to be able to continue patching them for a while yet.

34848592.title: campus tempo
34848592.description: Feet hurt on the raw spots. Moderate effort tempo on last 4 miles.

3907602.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
3907602.description: Greenway x 2.  Ran slow and easy, worked hard not to aggravate any of my quirky spots, mostly succeeded.

13617593.title: easy easy morning run
13617593.description: First run since doing the hard stadium stairs workout last weekend.  Nice and easy with some walking.  Foot was ok with no pain.  Legs were glad to be moving but had kinks and pains in unusual places.  If I go more than 4 days without running I wake up (like last night) with cramping.  I feel like I'll be ready to go for the race on Saturday.

14899218.title: Hogtown Creek Greenway
14899218.description: Slowed down and put in some more time in the heat.

6278689.description: Supposed to be my easy day, but saw Dan C. and his group turn onto the trail a little way ahead of me. Decided to catch up and run with them for a while (hunter instinct?).  See if you can figure out which loop that was.... loop splits (3.8 miles each):  41:02 / 31:14 / 35:19 / 36:14.  Beautiful day in the Hammock.  Trails are in great shape due to recent rain and it looks like they cleaned them off for the planned maintenance burns.  Didn't have any noticeable smoke smell.  My overall time includes the jog to the car and back for refueling.  Continuous forward motion...
6278689.title: San Felasco 4 x Hammock Cutoff loop

13175395.title: San Felasco south side to north side
13175395.description: A cold, grey, rainy day... perfect day for a trail run!  Ran from the south side of San Felasco (hiking trails) along the power lines to the north side, then did Hammock Hub and part of Tung Nut loop. Really fun run! The only tricky part was crossing the wilderness area.  I think my GPS cheated me out of some distance, especially on the twisty parts, since the legs felt strong and that I was moving better than 10:30 pace.  I saw deer and some feral pigs, very few humans.  Foot bothered me just a little bit during the run but didn't notice my ribs at all.  Wore my Soft Star Dash trail mocs in prep for upcoming Trail of Payne race... they rock!

13670855.description: I ran this Trail of Payne 10k more than a minute faster than last year.  Not bad considering it was my first race since November.  I stuck to my race plan pretty well and maintained fairly even splits: 6:35, 6:41, 6:32, 6:48, 6:42, 6:34, 1:10.  Wore my new New Balance Minimus Trail Zero MT00 shoes. They really are great shoes, especially for racing, since they are so lightweight. My legs felt like they were in good shape for this today, I recovered from last weekend's stadium workout just in time. I was able to score 2nd in my age group.
13670855.title: Trail of Payne 10k

3332487.title: hill repeats
3332487.description: Shands Hill (Newell Drive) x 5 with warm up and cool down.

31500453.title: out and back to Rock Trails
31500453.description: Long run in Altra Olympus. Included about a mile at the Rock Trails. I don't like them for a trail shoe due to the weight, tall stack height, and lack of traction on dirt, leaves, and grass. I think cushioned shoes cause more jarring in my upper body. Had to be very careful with my form. Noticed a pain in my ab muscles. Also developed a visual artifact (possibly due to broken capillary or something). High perceived effort by the end due to 77 degrees and 73% humidity. Drank no fuel or water for run.

24801272.title: another long run
24801272.description: Tired legs. Had some questionable pains in the beginning (upper left hammy in particular) but by 40 minutes in I was feeling good and loose.

36368111.description: Hard effort tempos at the end. Tough day. Biggest run in a long time.
36368111.title: San Felasco trail run

34100812.description: Run for Rehab 5k costume run. Legs were not fresh today but I enjoyed running as The Flash and winning the race overall!
34100812.title: Run for Rehab 5k costume race

23182970.description: This morning's moist air following the Tropical Storm felt good on my eyes. And (hee hee) no glasses fogging up.
23182970.title: first post-LASIK run

35667222.description: Some weather relief due to incoming storm. Humid but breezy.
35667222.title: campus progression

35559001.description: Hard Track workout 1 x 1600m, 12 x 200m. Full recovery after the 1600m, the 200m reps split into 2 sets of 6 each (200m rest between reps, 400m rest between sets).  1600m in 5:13. 200m Splits: 36,37,33,33,33,33,33,34,32,33,32,33. Tired from long weekend at the beach but made it through.
35559001.title: Track - 1 x 1600m, 12 x 200m

23370979.description: Exploring the paths (mostly crushed granite) on the north side of Lady Bird Lake in Austin, TX.
23370979.title: Lady Bird Lake trails

18211597.title: Track time trial 400m
18211597.description: Did a single 400m at Cone Park track.  69 seconds is a ways off from my personal best down around 53 seconds (college days back in the 90s).  edit: changed the time so this 400m doesn't end up the fastest mile pace.

19479295.title: lunch run through Morningside
19479295.description: Temps shot up and up . Wanted to get more miles today but the body was saying "enough". With the marathon less than 2 weeks away, time to ease into my taper. New shoes... NB Minimus Trail MT00, this time in green.

35325308.description: Nasty bug had me down all week. Didn't run, didn't want to run. This morning I felt a little better. It was cool and humid post-rain, a nice morning on the trails. Took it easy.
35325308.title: greenways

4544884.description: Mile Splits: 6:46, 6:14, 7:07.  Lots of slow bodies ahead of me at the start. It also looks like I died just a bit.
4544884.title: Zilker Holiday Tree 5k

5680760.description: Too much food and drink for dinner.
5680760.title: 8th Ave short flat

10077223.description: Yesterday I was very very sore from the long run on Sunday.  Just wanted to get the blood pumping a little this morning.
10077223.title: gentle 20 minutes

34103301.title: San Felasco trails long run
34103301.description: blue yellow blue yellow except I missed my turn on the second blue. Tired now!

4403107.description: Nice run with Matt C.  Rain was COLD.
4403107.title: San Felasco outer loop

32646089.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

32374933.description: Great hilly route on the unimproved roads south of Tuscawilla Lake.
32374933.title: TuscaHilla Micanopy Veterans Way hill loops

21043174.title: Track 6 x 1000m
21043174.description: I had a little trouble breathing this morning due to yesterday spending time in the crawl space under our house (dust and mold!).  Kept recovery short on these (200 m jog, avg. around 1:18 rest). Splits: 3:51, 3:56, 3:47, 3:51, 3:53, 3:43  (which works out to 6:20 - 5:58 per mile pace).

33113605.title: BRP
33113605.description: Included a solid 15 minutes of climbing.

10301055.title: John Holmes trail run
10301055.description: John Holmes trail run 16 Miler near Brooksville, FL (Croom hiking trails).  I was 3rd overall and was top in my age group.  Improved my time by over 20 minutes compared to last year.  Wore my Altra Instincts.  Tough tough race, lots o' pain.  In not atypical fashion I went out too fast and suffered for it. The winner (also from Gainesville) was haulin' ass.

33193865.title: 42nd Annual Granville Firecracker Five race
33193865.description: Nice cool morning for a July 4th race. Beautiful day for the Firecracker Five miler. Tough course with the first two miles of rolling uphill. Official results show 6th overall, won my age group, with a time of 29:54 (avg. sub-6 minute miles). Mile Splits: 6:07, 6:10, 5:59, 5:41, 5:57

36133317.description: Did not actually sprint but did 4 x steep hill strides. Working through some systematic malaise / fatigue / soreness.
36133317.title: steep hill strides x 4

2933197.description: Ran the rest of the way home holding my huaraches in my hands after they rubbed a raw spot between my toes.
2933197.title: Barefoot finish after huarache fail

25197161.description: Meh. Legs sluggish. Even stopped to walk a few times.
25197161.title: damp morning

35866730.description: Had the pace down to 7:30 for a few of the miles then the heat got to me.
35866730.title: hilly GNV

33171987.description: Repeat 1.15 mile loops on the grassy course trail. Splits: 9:27, 9:01, 8:27, 7:58.
33171987.title: BU XC course trail progression

6216418.description:
Aerobic hill repeats (full recovery in between each), one-third mile of gradual hill that turns into a steep grade near the top.  Six hills: 2:12 / 2:12 / 2:10 / 2:14 / 2:12 / 2:16   Recovery:  2:56 / 2:54 / 3:00 / 4:03 / 4:21 / ---
Really interesting to see how my recovery time increased towards the end.
6216418.title: one-third mile hill repeats

35517561.description: Track workout 6 x 600m at 3k pace with 200m rest. My target was 2:00 per rep (based on 17 minute 5k). First rep was spot on and got faster from there. First workout in spikes - New Balance MXC700BS (actually XC shoes but they worked fine). Good day, good workout. Splits: 2:00, 1:59, 1:58, 1:57, 1:56, 1:57
35517561.title: Track - 6 x 600m

24577445.title: San Felasco
24577445.description: Was just going to go for an easy trail run but after about 30 minutes in I felt so good that I decided to go go go, basically getting in a trail temp run. On my second loop I crossed paths with Meredith D. and ran the rest of the way with her. I feel good and ready for Friday's race.

19654516.description: Not exactly the way I want to feel the day before my marathon. Didn't sleep very well, woke up with a headache, generally feeling pretty grumpy. Legs not feeling fresh.
19654516.title: easy greenway

35264889.title: lunch run
35264889.description: Niggle in my right front hip flexor.

5587998.description: Had a few odd little twinges.  One in the knee, one in the glute.  Didn't seem to affect my race.
5587998.title: Warmup and cool down

30875391.description: Perfect morning for the Ravine Gardens Costume Run 6k race. The venue is just beautiful with the course running on the driving tour road around the ravine. Definitely some hills here! Loved the kids yelling "Here comes The Flash!" and "He's so Fast!". Won the 6k with a time of 22:30. My Altra 3-Sum shoes were specifically ordered to become part of my Flash racing outfit and I really like the way they feel.
30875391.title: Ravine Gardens Costume Run 6k race

17855671.description: Was just going to make this a slow recovery run but I ended up doing some pickups on the way back.
17855671.title: recovery run

4738285.title: brisk San Felasco blue loop
4738285.description: Matt C. tweaked his ankle so we stopped and walked for some of this.  Even though it was COLD we saw a barefoot runner.

26285353.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

32228050.description: Woke up and legs just kind of hurt while doing nothing, so I had to get out there and get some movement despite the pollen / allergy thing. Been doing a lot of sitting (at my computer) during the evenings lately, definitely killing me.
32228050.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop

35883283.description: Woke up with a twang in my uppper outside of my left leg... where the piriformis attaches I think. Just went nice and easy to loosen up and get some blood flow.
35883283.title: greenway and neighborhood

36269103.description: Coooool morning felt nice. Trail tempo x 2, each rep. approx 2 miles long. Splits: 14:37, 14:29
36269103.title: San Felasco trails tempo x 2

17508952.title: The Daily
17508952.description: Forgot to enter this in the AM.

36513491.description: Stadium consisted of 2 x up stairs, down bleachers. 4 x short stairs. 2 x up bleachers, down bleachers.  Down with slow eccentric movement to therapeurize my tendons and muscles. Fitness pit dips, pull-ups, push-ups, sit-ups.
36513491.title: stadium and fitness pit

23885524.description: Home to the Santa Fe water stop, back past the painted wall to campus, to Depot Ave., then to Boulware Springs water stop on the Gainesville-Hawthorne trail.
23885524.title: Long run

12285740.title: cold morning run
12285740.description: Tried to go easy but decided to cut it short anyway. I donated blood late yesterday afternoon and now feeling a little low on energy.

33865494.title: track workout 6 x 300m, 1600m, 6 x 300m
33865494.description: Track workout 6 x 300m, 1600m, 6 x 300m. 100m rest on the 300s, 500m rest before the 1600m. Splits: 56, 57, 57, 57, 58, 56, 5:47, 61, 61, 58, 61, 59, 59

21537473.description: Foggy! Definitely needed an easy recovery day after yesterday's race.
21537473.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back

35950884.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd ( Glen Springs Rd ) out and back

2228559.title: 1.5 barefoot
2228559.description: Coming off the damp greenway trail and hitting the concrete sidewalk on 8th Ave gave me blisters but did not realize until I got home and happened to look at the bottom of my foot.  Concrete was not bad at all in the shade.  My foot injury still hurts so I am a dumbass for running at all.

29028219.description: Barefoot recovery run. Still have some leg muscle soreness from the track meet on Thursday.
29028219.title: barefoot

5041079.title: greenway in mocs
5041079.description: I'm liking my RunAmocs for easy runs.

34349741.description: Started slow but felt ok after getting warmed up.
34349741.title: Moderate

19048868.title: greenway trails with kids
19048868.description: The kids are getting better at pacing themselves.

7583493.description: Since my Altra Instincts feel like they are going flat I decided to switch back to my VFF for a change. At the beginning everything felt good.  It was nice to sense the ground again.  I could feel the built-in spring of the foot, lower leg and tendons.  But after about 30 minutes my Achilles started to ache. Towards the end I had some discomfort in the arch and around the toe pockets.  I'm a bit frustrated with shoes right now.  Probably need to start rotating footwear again anyway to help minimize repetitive motion injuries.
7583493.title: VFF for the first time since April

10812359.title: Perfect cool running weather
10812359.description: First real test of my new Inov-8 Bare-X 150 shoes. Good shoes. They are breaking in nicely, definitely going to wear these for the half marathon next weekend. Long run round town and through campus.  Got to experience the sights and smells of Gator tailgating before the big homecoming football game.  Now, time for breakfast!

9628478.title: Stadium Stairs at the Swamp
9628478.description: Round trip to from stadium and 8 x stadium stairs.  Had a nice rainshower about halfway through to cool me off.  I think I'm ready to declare my Altra Instincts officially dead.  Disappointing cushion durability, but right now I'm leaning towards buying another pair.

19723360.description: Glad to be able to move in an almost normal fashion. Still have muscle soreness and tenderness in the joints, etc.
19723360.title: walk with some jog and strides

17531833.title: barefoot beach run at Anastasia Island
17531833.description: The water was way up today and in many places was washing right up to the dunes. For a lot of the run there wasn't any hard-packed surface and I was either splashing or plodding. It was warm but there was a nice breeze. The beach conditions made for a great workout. Toes are a little tender after that much barefooting in sand.

11073570.title: Glen Springs Rd. Loop
11073570.description: This was supposed to be LSD but I just wasn't feeling it today so I did not run very long.

35895128.title: steep hill sprints and fitness pit

7462773.title: Brywood to NW 31st Blvd (Glen Springs Rd) out and back
7462773.description: Recovery run. Still sore and stiff from Monday's race.

34150382.description: Warmed up quickly during the last loop, over 80 degrees by the time we finished.
34150382.title: San Felasco trails

4986545.title: tweaked something
4986545.description: I guess the playground sprinting caught up with me today. Overall mileage was also a big jump over last week (since my Achilles is getting better).  Tweaked something in my upper hamstring or hip / glute area.  Walked a little and then was able to jog the last 1.5 miles home.   I need to watch those week-to-week mileage increases.

33686030.title: San Felasco trails
33686030.description: Great morning, good conversations. Lots of runners there for Richard Gerand's group. So much for the 10 percent rule about weekly mileage increases.

2973661.description: Burning off those extra pieces of pizza I ate for dinner.
2973661.title: Brywood to 13th St

34977752.title: short steep hill sprints x 6
34977752.description: short steep hill sprints x 6 and then to Burrito Bros. Richard G. was in beast mode and I could not beat him up the hill. May have run these just a scooch too hard.

7694890.description: Lot's of blah runs lately.  Either this is my body telling me its time to take off a few weeks with complete rest due to longterm muscle fatigue (e.g. overtraining syndrome), or my central governor is pissed about the pain I suffered during my last race.  I'm sure the heat doesn't help.  Ran in my RunAmoc DASH, it's a nice shoe.
7694890.title: no sidewalks

35024744.title: steep hill sprints
35024744.description: Gonna try to make this a regular Monday thing. Felt really slow and off today post-race. Stopped at 5 reps.

2656694.title: VFF run including a couple intervals
2656694.description: I was going to say we did two .3 mile tempo runs during this, but then I looked up the term "tempo run" and realized I was misusing it.  Whatever they are called, we did two sections of faster pace in the middle.  I think we hit 7 minute per mile pace during the fast parts.  I developed TOFP towards the end.  Time to take a day off.

31395207.title: school grounds xc course and HILL

33294928.title: Stadium stairs
33294928.description: 5 x stadium stairs full. quads still sore so I skipped the bottom sprints.

20290221.description: Wow, over 200 miles on my Altra Samsons.
20290221.title: warm up and down

15162562.title: long tempo run
15162562.description: Trying to correct some of my minor form issues that I noticed in the high speed video I received from the UF Ortho study.  The two big things were 1. I had asymmetric arm carriage 2. I had completely lost the "falling forward" pattern. I noticed while running tonight that falling forward encourages "popping" the feet back up off the ground more quickly. I remember that! But I had not been doing it. I wore my Altra Sampsons for the first time in a while. I think my previous Achilles complaints from these shoes stemmed from the fact that I was doing it wrong. Better form = no pains. It also means faster pace with less effort.

14352166.title: Fallen Heroes 5k
14352166.description: Fallen Heroes 5k. YEAH! Huge Personal Record (this decade) with a time of 18:17... almost 50 seconds faster than my previous best 5k time. Ran the first two miles under control (5:59, 6:04) and the last mile I was trying to chase down the guy in front of me. Didn't let myself fall off the pace during mile 3, kept yelling at myself to go go go and fought through the pain. I was mentally ready for this one today. I wanted that elusive sub-19 minute 5k and got it!  Last mile must have been haulin'. Earned 4th overall and 2nd in my age group. Inov-8 Bare-X 150 are great road racing shoes.

I'm a little disappointed I didn't improve my 5k time since I know I'm getting back into serious shape (it's probably been 15 years since I have been this fit). I gave a damn hard effort tonight and won my age group (30-39). I think I placed pretty well overall (still waiting to see the results). My NB Minimus Trail Zero shoes were great for this terrain.
